, with no mechanistic detail provided.', NULL, '{a2c9f06c-7993-4e4b-bf9b-a3123e7a0764}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:04.177566+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:04.177728+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('85b2f933-d559-4815-8b5c-93ba9ad45081', '9c1bbc74-1113-49bf-bde7-6a4839ba970a', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single source (Open Targets) and a single mechanistic line is provided, naming CORTICOTROPIN as an MC2R agonist clinical candidate for PCOS. No independent mechanistic lines converge; there is no corroborating data beyond the database listing.', 'The single claim is a database annotation of clinical stage (EARLY_PHASE_1) and mechanism, with no human, animal, or in-vitro experimental data presented. No study design or model strength is described to support rigor.', 'The claim specifies a precise molecular action: Melanocortin receptor 2 agonist acting on the melanocortin 2 receptor (MC2R). This is a clearly defined single target and mechanism.', 'MC2R is the ACTH receptor driving adrenal steroidogenesis, which is mechanistically relevant to androgen excess in PCOS, lending some target-phenotype fit. However, an MC2R agonist would be expected to increase adrenal steroid output, so the directional benefit for PCOS is not established by the single claim.', 'With only one claim there are no multiple signals to compare, so consistency cannot be meaningfully assessed; nothing contradicts, but nothing converges either.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'CORTICOTROPIN is listed by Open Targets as an early-phase (EARLY_PHASE_1) clinical candidate for PCOS acting as a melanocortin 2 receptor agonist.', 'CORTICOTROPIN agonizes the melanocortin 2 (ACTH) receptor, modulating adrenal steroidogenesis relevant to androgen-related PCOS pathophysiology.', '{fbfb4da3-dda4-4de9-b331-d9301a4fcd6e}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:05.714458+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:05.714486+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('60b8732b-7d72-4018-8f1f-fde4942404bf', 'e566f424-c6ab-4fbd-9cdd-98821fcd8788', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single source (Open Targets database annotation) is cited, providing one line of evidence linking the drug to a target. No independent mechanistic lines converge in the claim set.', 'The claim reflects a database-curated clinical candidate annotation citing a PHASE_3 maximum clinical stage, which is human-relevant, but no actual study data, design, or outcomes are described. The evidence is purely a target-drug association without supporting experimental detail.', 'The claim specifies a precise mechanism of action: GnRH receptor agonist acting on the gonadotropin releasing hormone receptor. This is a clearly named, specific drug-target relationship.', 'GnRH receptor modulation is biologically connected to the hypothalamic-pituitary-ovarian axis relevant to PCOS, supporting target-phenotype fit. However, the single annotation does not establish a clear therapeutic direction or phenotype linkage beyond a candidate listing.', 'With only one claim there is no opportunity for multiple mechanistic signals to agree or disagree. The single statement is internally coherent but cannot demonstrate convergence.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, gonadorelin acetate is a Phase 3 clinical candidate for PCOS acting as a GnRH receptor agonist on the gonadotropin releasing hormone receptor.', 'Agonism of the gonadotropin releasing hormone receptor modulates the hypothalamic-pituitary-ovarian axis, potentially influencing gonadotropin secretion relevant to PCOS.', '{a97d0a87-5c57-4299-9225-2b872ad22ec7}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:06.596341+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:06.596369+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('50c4b81b-3a29-4e5b-a7e2-a02ea54ec6ff', '5f2390ac-13e2-4e33-8c98-515e7f1fe1a7', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The single verified claim only states that KISSPEPTIN-10 is a Phase 1 clinical candidate for PCOS per Open Targets. No mechanistic lines of evidence are described, so there is no convergence of independent pathways to assess.', 'The claim is a database registry entry indicating clinical stage, not a study with a human-relevant model or experimental data. No model rigor or recency of mechanistic evidence is reported.', 'The claim provides no information on how kisspeptin-10 acts on any molecular target. There is no description of receptor binding or target specificity in the verified claim.', 'While kisspeptin signaling is biologically related to reproductive hormone regulation, the verified claim itself offers no target-phenotype mechanism linking the drug to PCOS pathology. Nothing in the quote supports a plausibility judgment.', 'Only one registry claim is present, so there are no multiple mechanistic signals to evaluate for directional agreement. Consistency cannot be established from a single non-mechanistic statement.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, KISSPEPTIN-10 is listed as a Phase 1 clinical candidate for PCOS, but no mechanistic data are provided.', NULL, '{33ffd360-3568-476c-b386-fec6bcd8f4b6}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:12.781467+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:12.781516+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c07d2d7b-3342-4123-bd80-714cd64cc061', '901054e4-34cb-4773-ac71-e9bfb2efbee0', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is provided — an Open Targets database entry listing menotropins as an FSH receptor agonist clinical candidate for PCOS. No independent mechanistic lines converge; there is just one annotation.', 'The evidence is a database annotation citing a clinical development stage (PHASE_2_3), which implies human-relevant context, but no actual study data, model, or experimental result is presented. The claim is purely a registry-level statement.', 'The claim explicitly states a defined mechanism: follicle stimulating hormone receptor agonist acting on the FSH receptor target. This is a specific, named molecular target and action.', 'FSH receptor agonism is mechanistically relevant to follicular development, which is central to PCOS ovulation induction, so the target-phenotype fit is reasonable. However, the claim offers no phenotypic linkage data beyond the registry entry asserting candidate status.', 'There is only one mechanistic signal (FSH receptor agonism), so there are no conflicting signals, but also nothing to corroborate directionality. Consistency cannot be meaningfully assessed across multiple lines from a single annotation.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Menotropins is listed in Open Targets as a Phase 2/3 clinical candidate for PCOS acting as a follicle stimulating hormone receptor agonist on the FSH receptor.', 'Menotropins agonizes the FSH receptor, stimulating ovarian follicular development, which is mechanistically relevant to ovulation induction in PCOS.', '{7b447c1b-9ecd-48f4-b664-adf79f1b23c5}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:13.524007+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:13.524045+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('2265582c-3b70-4018-b8db-0a4d3ab5ac1b', 'afe89892-83af-4c18-a34a-02c048f8e7e8', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single source (Open Targets) is cited, providing one line of evidence (a drug-target-indication association). No independent mechanistic lines converge here; it is a single database annotation.', 'The claim reflects a clinical candidate at EARLY_PHASE_1 stage for PCOS, which is human-relevant in intent, but no actual study data, models, or outcomes are provided—only a database annotation of clinical stage.', 'The mechanism is highly specific: ganirelix acetate acts as a gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor antagonist on the GnRH receptor, a precisely named molecular target per the Open Targets claim.', 'GnRH receptor antagonism is mechanistically relevant to PCOS given the role of LH/FSH dysregulation, and the EARLY_PHASE_1 listing supports a plausible target-phenotype fit, but no phenotypic or outcome data are shown to confirm benefit.', 'There is only one claim, so no conflicting signals exist, but a single annotation cannot demonstrate convergence of multiple mechanistic signals pointing the same way.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Ganirelix acetate is listed as an early-phase clinical candidate for PCOS acting as a gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor antagonist per Open Targets.', 'By antagonizing the GnRH receptor, ganirelix acetate suppresses pituitary gonadotropin (LH/FSH) release, potentially correcting the LH-driven hormonal dysregulation characteristic of PCOS.', '{4df41f63-a847-4a96-b04e-39fb84fc5063}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:16.841296+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:16.841331+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('2cbe92cd-824d-4d18-8899-a62efd4c59d9', 'e75c7096-244d-48fc-a574-1ff3c1e1d135', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only a single claim is provided, indicating UBIDECARENONE is a clinical candidate for PCOS at phase 2/3. No mechanistic lines of evidence are described, so there is no convergence of independent mechanisms.', 'The single claim is a database annotation from Open Targets about clinical stage, not data from any human, animal, or in-vitro model. No model strength or recency of mechanistic evidence is provided.', 'No molecular target or mechanism of action is named in the claim. There is no information on how specifically the drug acts on any PCOS-relevant target.', 'The claim provides no mechanism or target-phenotype linkage, only that the compound is in clinical development for PCOS. Without any described pathway, target-phenotype fit cannot be assessed.', 'Only one claim exists and it contains no mechanistic signal, so there is nothing to assess for directional agreement among mechanistic signals.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, ubidecarenone is a phase 2/3 clinical candidate for PCOS, but no mechanistic pathway evidence is provided.', NULL, '{cab30892-8b78-47b9-9847-2f132abf6a31}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:21.272846+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:21.272910+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('9316ad00-b436-45bf-943c-cf6de56e041d', '4f298539-db26-48e8-b86e-bbc7c69884a9', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is present: an Open Targets database entry stating ESTRADIOL VALERATE is an ERα agonist clinical candidate for PCOS. No independent mechanistic lines converge to support this.', 'The claim derives from a curated database entry citing an EARLY_PHASE_1 clinical stage, which implies some human-relevant development context, but no actual experimental model, data, or outcomes are described to assess strength or recency.', 'The mechanism is precisely named: estrogen receptor alpha agonist acting on target estrogen receptor 1 (ESR1), a well-defined molecular target rather than a vague mechanism.', 'Estrogen receptor signaling is biologically relevant to reproductive/ovarian physiology underlying PCOS, lending some target-phenotype fit, but the single claim provides no mechanistic linkage explaining how ERα agonism modifies PCOS pathology.', 'With only one claim there is no opportunity for signals to converge or conflict; the single statement is internally consistent but cannot demonstrate cross-source agreement.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Estradiol valerate is listed as an early-phase clinical candidate for PCOS acting as an estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1) agonist.', 'Estradiol valerate may modulate PCOS-related reproductive physiology via agonism of estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1).', '{7bbfd71b-eada-49ed-97d0-3b5517d1cf7a}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:22.822116+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:22.822151+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('2d13609f-5d99-4afa-b2bd-8c81f6c6225e', '70176fbe-64a8-401a-b4e4-36a3fd33ab43', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single Open Targets database entry is provided, stating Pavinetant is a Phase 2 candidate for PCOS with NK3R antagonism. No independent mechanistic lines converge; there is just one annotation source.', 'The claim references a clinical development stage (Phase 2) and a defined human target, suggesting human-relevant context, but no actual study data, model, or outcome is presented—only a database mechanism-of-action annotation.', 'The claim names a precise molecular action: Neurokinin 3 receptor antagonist on target tachykinin receptor 3 (TACR3). This is a highly specific, well-defined drug-target relationship.', 'NK3R antagonism is mechanistically relevant to PCOS via modulation of GnRH/LH secretion through KNDy neurons, and Pavinetant is listed as a PCOS clinical candidate. However, the single claim asserts target identity without demonstrating the target-to-phenotype effect.', 'There is only one signal, so it cannot conflict, but neither does it form a converging set. The lone annotation is internally coherent but provides no corroborating directional evidence.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Pavinetant is a Phase 2 small-molecule clinical candidate for PCOS that acts as a Neurokinin 3 receptor (TACR3) antagonist.', 'By antagonizing the neurokinin 3 receptor (TACR3) on KNDy neurons, Pavinetant may modulate GnRH/LH pulsatility implicated in PCOS pathophysiology.', '{81475410-6d71-4f3f-96da-b008b440f433}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:24.683631+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:24.683663+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('44192149-54f2-4f95-8d15-ff394285c39a', '77d8a832-5d66-44cc-bc19-56d50ea95322', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is provided: a database annotation that SMC021 is a calcitonin receptor agonist developed for menopause. No independent mechanistic studies or converging lines are cited.', 'The sole source is an Open Targets database annotation listing clinical stage and mechanism; no experimental model, trial data, or human-relevant outcome study is presented to assess strength or recency.', 'The claim names a defined molecular target (calcitonin receptor) and a specific action (agonist), giving moderate target specificity, but no data quantifying selectivity or off-target effects are provided.', 'Calcitonin receptor agonism has a plausible link to postmenopausal bone metabolism, and the candidate reached Phase 2 for menopause, but the single annotation does not connect the target to a specific menopausal phenotype or outcome.', 'There is only one claim, so there is no conflict, but neither is there corroborating signal; the lone annotation is internally consistent but cannot demonstrate converging direction.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, SMC021 is a calcitonin receptor agonist that reached Phase 2 clinical development for menopause.', 'SMC021 acts as a calcitonin receptor agonist, a pathway implicated in bone metabolism relevant to postmenopausal conditions.', '{ee5e5ba4-7e0e-48d1-8f56-e89c05ca6182}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:25.663712+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:25.663751+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('aa7095f1-c128-4048-8ea2-3a4af89278fb', '13998085-3d51-40d8-807f-ad408d63ac4e', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 1, 2, 1, 'Only a single source (Open Targets) and a single mechanistic statement are provided. There is no convergence of independent mechanistic lines, just one drug-target-indication annotation.', 'The claim reflects a curated database annotation citing a PHASE_2 clinical stage, which implies human-relevant data exists, but no actual study model, data, or experimental detail is given. The evidence is a registry-level annotation rather than a described model.', 'Estriol is described as an estrogen receptor modulator acting on estrogen receptor 2 (ERβ), which names a specific target. However, estriol is broadly an estrogen agonist acting across estrogen receptors, so action is not highly selective to a single named target.', 'Estrogen receptor modulation is a well-established and direct mechanistic fit for menopause, a condition of estrogen decline. The target-phenotype relationship (estrogen receptor activity in menopause) is highly coherent.', 'There is only one positive mechanistic signal, so there is nothing contradictory, but consistency across multiple signals cannot be assessed with a single claim. The lone signal points coherently toward an estrogenic mechanism.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, estriol is a Phase 2 clinical candidate for menopause acting as an estrogen receptor modulator on estrogen receptor 2.', 'Estriol acts as an estrogen receptor (ERβ) modulator, supplementing declining estrogen activity to address menopausal symptoms.', '{b406e137-fd24-4d41-9ec0-852c050b6159}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:32.569090+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:32.569151+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('7067b52a-4e11-40eb-ac17-2d8f4007e4c2', 'afa0f645-cd9d-46fa-b11a-38e0b0d5071a', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only a single claim is provided, a database registry entry from Open Targets indicating clinical stage. No independent mechanistic lines converge; there is no description of any pathway, target engagement, or biological mechanism.', 'The sole claim is an Open Targets database annotation of clinical-stage status, not an experimental model. No human, animal, or in-vitro mechanistic data are presented to assess model strength.', 'No target is named and no mechanism of action is described for NITRIC ACID. The claim only states a clinical candidate status, providing no information on specificity of action on any named target.', 'There is no stated target-phenotype relationship; the claim simply asserts candidate status for menopause. Without any mechanistic detail, target-phenotype fit cannot be supported.', 'With only one registry claim and no mechanistic signals, there is nothing to evaluate for directional agreement. No converging or conflicting evidence is present.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per an Open Targets registry entry, NITRIC ACID is listed as a Phase 2 clinical candidate for menopause, with no mechanistic detail provided.', NULL, '{c7ee252e-8a88-4866-ae91-e4290ccafd9b}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:32.997212+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:32.997226+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c6cb66c4-1497-4fee-99ef-9b5d2012689c', 'bc13ec6f-16f8-4001-b8b1-a7b165519dc1', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is provided: an Open Targets database entry naming desvenlafaxine succinate as a serotonin transporter inhibitor and a Phase 3 candidate for menopause. No independent mechanistic studies converge to corroborate the pathway.', 'The claim cites a curated database entry (Open Targets) noting a maximum clinical stage of Phase 3, implying human clinical development, which is human-relevant. However, no actual study models, data, or mechanistic experiments are presented—only a target-disease association annotation.', 'The claim specifies a precise mechanism—serotonin transporter (SLC6A4) inhibition—which is a well-defined molecular target for desvenlafaxine. This is a highly specific drug-target action statement.', 'Serotonin transporter inhibition is mechanistically plausible for vasomotor menopausal symptoms, and the Phase 3 status supports target-phenotype fit. However, the single claim does not articulate how SERT inhibition links to the menopause phenotype beyond the database association.', 'There is only one mechanistic signal (SERT inhibition), so directionality cannot be cross-checked against other lines. The single statement is internally consistent but provides no convergence to assess.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Desvenlafaxine succinate is a Phase 3 clinical candidate for menopause acting via serotonin transporter (SLC6A4) inhibition per Open Targets.', 'Inhibition of the serotonin transporter (SLC6A4) increases synaptic serotonin, which may modulate hypothalamic thermoregulatory pathways underlying menopausal vasomotor symptoms.', '{8611dccf-7004-42e8-97ee-35d45ab2ffe1}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:33.551346+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:33.551359+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('277e9fcf-e984-48c9-8794-3139ffdbcf6d', 'df468fdc-297f-4a39-913c-8f0cf50ee3e5', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 1, 1, 2, 2, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is presented: an Open Targets annotation linking BAZEDOXIFENE to menopause via estrogen receptor modulation. There is one mechanistic line (ER modulation), not multiple independent converging lines, but it is a recognized target-disease association.', 'The claim derives from a curated database (Open Targets) citing clinical-stage development (PHASE_3) for menopause, which is human-relevant. However, no actual study, model, or experimental data are provided, limiting confidence in rigor.', 'The claim names a precise mechanism (Estrogen receptor modulator) on a specific target (estrogen receptor 2 / ESR2), making the drug-target action highly specific as stated.', 'Estrogen receptor modulation is a mechanistically well-fit pathway for menopause, a condition defined by declining estrogen activity. The target-phenotype fit is strong and biologically coherent.', 'With only one claim, there is no opportunity for multiple signals to agree or disagree; the single annotation is internally consistent but cannot demonstrate convergence.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'BAZEDOXIFENE is a phase-3 clinical candidate for menopause acting as an estrogen receptor modulator targeting estrogen receptor 2.', 'BAZEDOXIFENE modulates estrogen receptor 2 (ESR2) signaling, compensating for declining estrogen activity associated with menopause.', '{b90e4e6a-87ec-404f-99d2-b9fe521351b4}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:35.245398+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:35.245415+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('b588b6f9-d2b1-4c22-aa15-7860312f44d1', '041510d6-ac3c-4f73-8511-df8e44d5eb60', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 2, 1, 'Only a single mechanistic line is provided: ESTRADIOL as an estrogen receptor alpha agonist on ESR1 per Open Targets. No independent converging lines of evidence are presented.', 'The claim derives from a curated database (Open Targets) noting approval status, but no specific human study, model, or experimental data is cited. This is an annotation rather than a strength-graded mechanistic model.', 'The action is described as a specific estrogen receptor alpha agonist on the named target estrogen receptor 1 (ESR1), giving a clearly defined drug-target interaction.', 'Estradiol acting as an ER-alpha agonist fits the menopause phenotype, which is driven by declining estrogen; the target-phenotype fit is strong and well established, and the drug has reached APPROVAL stage for menopause.', 'With only one mechanistic claim there is nothing to contradict, but also no multiple signals to confirm directional agreement. The single statement is internally coherent.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Estradiol is an approved estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1) agonist indicated for menopause.', 'Estradiol restores declining estrogen signaling in menopause by acting as an agonist at estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1).', '{f446f992-066d-4c84-8a07-db6040b406db}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:41.641445+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:41.641789+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a789f7bf-43fc-48e2-9105-c5eb9c01cf39', '4f298539-db26-48e8-b86e-bbc7c69884a9', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 1, 1, 2, 2, 1, 'Only a single mechanistic line is provided: Open Targets linking estradiol valerate to ESR1 as an ERα agonist. There are no independent converging sources or pathways, so corroboration is limited to one annotation.', 'The claim is drawn from a curated database (Open Targets) reflecting clinical approval status rather than a specific human or in-vitro experiment. It is human-relevant in that it reflects an approved indication, but no primary study model or data is described, limiting rigor.', 'The mechanism is precisely named: ERα agonism on the specific target estrogen receptor 1 (ESR1). This is a clearly specified drug-target action.', 'Estrogen receptor agonism is a well-established and biologically coherent mechanism for treating menopause, which involves declining estrogen. The target-phenotype fit is strong and the drug is approved for this indication.', 'There is only one mechanistic signal (ERα agonism), so there is nothing to be inconsistent with; the single signal aligns with the menopause phenotype but consistency cannot be evaluated across multiple lines.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Estradiol valerate is an approved clinical agent for menopause acting as an estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1) agonist.', 'Estradiol valerate replaces declining endogenous estrogen by agonizing estrogen receptor alpha (ESR1), restoring estrogen-dependent signaling in menopause.', '{bebf0c4a-7f6b-45aa-8710-3462846bd47d}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:41.982751+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:41.982785+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('6be693aa-29b8-4a21-b6df-19ad98637582', 'd735fc43-3ce2-4d25-864b-7766bf050f78', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only a single claim is provided, stating that ISOFLAVONE is a Phase 3 clinical candidate for menopause per Open Targets. No mechanistic lines of evidence are described, so no convergence can be assessed.', 'The claim merely references a database entry on clinical development stage; it provides no model data, no preclinical or clinical results, and no mechanistic detail. There is nothing to gauge model strength or human relevance beyond a development-stage label.', 'No molecular target or mechanism of action is named in the claim. The text does not describe how isoflavone acts on any specific target relevant to menopause.', 'Although isoflavones are plausibly relevant to menopause (phytoestrogenic activity), the provided claim contains no target-phenotype fit information. The Phase 3 status alone does not establish a mechanistic plausibility within the claims shown.', 'With only one non-mechanistic claim, there are no multiple signals to compare, so directional consistency cannot be evaluated.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'ISOFLAVONE is listed as a Phase 3 clinical candidate for menopause per Open Targets, but no mechanistic or outcome data are provided.', NULL, '{dd24836f-0478-4a4a-b0de-d296b8262fcb}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:43.543323+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:43.543362+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('56967661-ab59-4f08-9620-b66bf8462c88', '6f07bf3d-46a6-408b-b253-a6bd96a6d4d7', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single line of evidence is present: one Open Targets annotation stating NORETHINDRONE is a progesterone receptor agonist clinical candidate for menopause. No independent mechanistic lines converge.', 'The claim is a curated database annotation reporting a PHASE_3 clinical stage for menopause, implying human-relevant development, but no actual study model, data, or experimental result is described. This is registry/annotation-level evidence rather than a strong mechanistic or clinical model.', 'The claim names a specific molecular action: progesterone receptor agonist acting on the progesterone receptor target. This is a clearly specified drug-target relationship.', 'Progesterone receptor agonism fits the menopausal hormone therapy context where a progestin is used, but the claim does not articulate how this action addresses a menopausal phenotype. The target-phenotype link is implied but not demonstrated by the single annotation.', 'There is only one signal, so there is nothing to contradict, but also no convergence to confirm directional consistency. A lone annotation cannot establish that multiple mechanistic signals agree.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Per Open Targets, NORETHINDRONE is a Phase 3 clinical candidate for menopause acting as a progesterone receptor agonist.', 'NORETHINDRONE agonizes the progesterone receptor, supplying progestational activity relevant to menopausal hormone therapy.', '{ea8d8516-ba67-4edb-a6ff-3777c78d63ec}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:05:46.113355+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:05:46.113375+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
