n, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Goserelin is annotated in Open Targets as a Phase 2/3 clinical candidate for adenomyosis acting as a gonadotropin-releasing hormone receptor agonist.', 'As a GnRH receptor agonist, goserelin downregulates pituitary gonadotropin release and induces a hypoestrogenic state, suppressing the estrogen-dependent ectopic endometrial tissue underlying adenomyosis.', '{a6949197-d121-4992-968c-64ca2305ec8f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:15.820875+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:15.820888+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('9c6cf41d-3553-4802-9a6b-ac1583a93e1e', 'c1bdf08b-2fd2-4d31-9ec9-a88972fa1322', '61143789-de48-488b-968b-f3f71189f1bc', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 0, 1, 1, 1, 'Only a single mechanistic line is provided: BROMOCRIPTINE as a D2-like dopamine receptor agonist on DRD2 (claim 1). No independent converging lines are presented.', 'The only evidence is a database annotation from Open Targets listing a maximum clinical stage of PHASE_1, with no described study, model, or human outcome data. There is no mechanistic or experimental model evidence to assess relevance or recency.', 'The claim names a defined target (dopamine receptor D2) and a defined action (D2-like agonist), giving moderate target specificity. However, ''D2-like'' agonism implies action across the broader D2-family, limiting true selectivity.', 'Bromocriptine being a listed Phase 1 clinical candidate for adenomyosis (claim 1) suggests a presumed target-phenotype link, plausibly via prolactin suppression. But no mechanistic data connecting DRD2 agonism to adenomyosis pathology is provided.', 'With only one annotation there is nothing contradictory, but also no multiple signals to confirm directional agreement. Consistency cannot be meaningfully demonstrated from a single source.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Bromocriptine is annotated as a Phase 1 clinical candidate for adenomyosis acting as a D2-like dopamine receptor agonist on DRD2.', 'Bromocriptine activates dopamine receptor D2 (D2-like agonism), which may suppress prolactin and dopaminergic pathways relevant to adenomyosis.', '{00ffb15c-e76c-4087-996c-0ae124bc67bd}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:22.064124+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:22.064170+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('88e962f6-a900-43d9-81b4-70b8d6afd880', '7330eec6-af95-4731-a824-f9eca7fc8ae6', '61143789-de48-488b-968b-f3f71189f1bc', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Only a single Open Targets database entry is provided, describing one mechanistic line (COX inhibition on PTGS2). No independent converging lines of evidence are present in the claims.', 'The claim references a clinical candidate at EARLY_PHASE_1 stage per Open Targets, which implies human-relevant clinical context but at the earliest stage. There is no experimental data, study, or model detail to assess strength.', 'Aspirin''s mechanism is stated as a cyclooxygenase inhibitor acting on PTGS2 (COX-2), a named target. However, aspirin is a well-known nonspecific COX inhibitor (COX-1 and COX-2), so its action on the named target is not highly specific.', 'COX-2/prostaglandin inhibition plausibly relates to inflammation and pain in adenomyosis, and the entry lists it as a candidate for adenomyosis. The claim asserts a target-phenotype association but provides no phenotypic or mechanistic detail linking PTGS2 inhibition to adenomyosis pathology.', 'There is only one mechanistic signal (COX/PTGS2 inhibition), so there is no conflict, but also no multiple signals to corroborate directional agreement. Consistency cannot be strongly established from a single database entry.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Aspirin is listed in Open Targets as an early-phase (EARLY_PHASE_1) clinical candidate for adenomyosis acting via cyclooxygenase (PTGS2/COX-2) inhibition.', 'Aspirin inhibits cyclooxygenase (PTGS2/COX-2), reducing prostaglandin synthesis that may drive inflammation and pain in adenomyosis.', '{b0edb12d-42df-414f-b349-7e55be8477df}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:23.803119+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:23.803151+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c9ff6fe9-5c96-4b45-af44-9e5c60801a6c', 'e4ea5770-4d2c-4e3d-8b95-defada7816b8', '61143789-de48-488b-968b-f3f71189f1bc', 'other', 'pathway', 0, 1, 1, 2, 1, 'Only a single source (Open Targets) provides one line of evidence: a database annotation that ULIPRISTAL ACETATE is a progesterone receptor modulator clinical candidate for adenomyosis. No independent mechanistic lines converge to support the claim.', 'The evidence is a clinical-stage annotation (PHASE_2 candidate) rather than in-vitro data, which is human-relevant, but it is a bare database listing with no actual study results, models, or outcomes reported.', 'The mechanism is stated as ''Progesterone receptor modulator on target progesterone receptor,'' which names a defined target. However, selective progesterone receptor modulators have mixed agonist/antagonist activity and the annotation provides no detail on selectivity of action.', 'Adenomyosis is a progesterone/estrogen-dependent uterine disorder, so a progesterone receptor modulator acting on the progesterone receptor has a strong target-phenotype fit, consistent with its PHASE_2 clinical candidate status for this condition.', 'With only one positive claim from a single source, there are no conflicting signals, but there is also no convergence of multiple mechanistic signals to assess consistency meaningfully.', 'F4', 0.75, 'Female representation not stated — applicability to women uncertain (flagged for full text).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Ulipristal acetate is a progesterone receptor modulator acting on the progesterone receptor and is a Phase 2 clinical candidate for adenomyosis per Open Targets.', 'As a selective progesterone receptor modulator, ulipristal acetate acts on the progesterone receptor to modulate progesterone signaling in adenomyotic endometrial/myometrial tissue.', '{42f5742f-346f-4d14-841e-bdbc2da2caeb}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:24.646025+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:24.646047+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('8bd9dc2c-4761-46eb-b26c-c8af6339aa37', '00ab920a-db04-48bf-9df9-eaca7bcc196b', '877f97b2-9c77-419e-89e0-c5460e74b245', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The single source is a systematic review, which scores 1 (one synthesis is not independent replication). Only one claim from one review supports the finding.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as rigor level 2 by design. However, the depth of the underlying evidence is not detailed in the claims.', 'Both vitamin B6 and anxiety are named directly in the claim (''Older women experienced anxiety reduction using vitamin B6'').', 'No mechanism is asserted or explained in the claims linking vitamin B6 to anxiety reduction. The quote only states an observed outcome without any mechanistic basis.', 'Only a single claim from a single source is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed; per rules this scores 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that vitamin B6 supplementation was associated with reduced anxiety in older women.', NULL, '{32c06d9a-255c-4c6e-acc9-3e84dbab20bd}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:28.450501+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:28.450637+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c2aebe3d-29d6-4b38-916e-54510c0c4408', '65dbde60-df59-465a-9e41-c1e1c01fbd56', '877f97b2-9c77-419e-89e0-c5460e74b245', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Only a single systematic review is cited, and it reports a negative finding (''not folate or vitamin B12''). A single synthesis is not independent replication, and the claim concerns stress in women rather than directly establishing anxiety efficacy, so corroboration is minimal.', 'The source is described as a systematic review, but the verbatim quote is a fragment (''not folate or vitamin B12'') that provides no detail on pooled study designs or analytic rigor. Given the weak, negative framing and lack of supporting detail, this is scored at the lower end.', 'Folate is named directly, but the underlying source addresses ''stress levels in women'' rather than anxiety as a clinical condition. The claim asserts no anxiety reduction, but the link between folate and anxiety specifically is not firmly established by the quote.', 'No mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the claims; the quote merely states folate does not reduce anxiety. There is no biological rationale provided to support an effect.', 'Only a single source is present, so directional consistency across independent studies cannot be assessed and is scored neutrally per the n/a rule.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review found that folate did not reduce anxiety/stress in older women.', NULL, '{402012ee-d4c9-4de8-9d1b-fff46261f4d9}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:32.058873+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:32.058949+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('af3abf6b-9cf3-4c4a-9464-01e16fde8f6a', '6701818c-d9fb-481e-a045-61939dc07893', '997ae490-b540-4e1e-ac1b-fbbac34448d3', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'All four claims derive from a SINGLE systematic review, which scores 1 — one synthesis is not independent replication. No additional independent studies are presented.', 'The source is a systematic review (''a systematic review''), which qualifies as rigor 2 by design. However, no individual trial details, effect sizes, or risk-of-bias assessments are provided in the claims.', 'The claims directly name essential fatty acids and premenstrual women/premenstrual syndrome (''premenstrual or menopausal anxiety'', ''anxiety in premenstrual women''). Both intervention and condition are explicitly stated.', 'The claims report an efficacy finding (reduced anxiety) but assert no mechanism for how EFAs act on premenstrual symptoms. No biochemical or physiological pathway is described.', 'Evidence is from a single review and findings are somewhat qualified — effective for anxiety but ''ineffective when depression was disregarded'' / only ''in the absence of depression''. With one source and conditional results, consistency defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review suggests essential fatty acids may reduce premenstrual anxiety in women without depression.', NULL, '{2fdfa05c-6431-4920-9059-775450efdf8b,ee6390bc-39b9-4e18-8fe2-0f0cbc165c03,6bbf8315-bcf1-410e-a8bf-0c661f7eb34b,11bc24f2-ae5d-40aa-b29b-a617dc785462}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:32.083291+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:32.083313+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('6f12ee0e-e7b0-4815-868f-7f8414e0cef4', '8c766160-d575-47e2-8ffc-bfd512899b30', '877f97b2-9c77-419e-89e0-c5460e74b245', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 1, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review which by definition is not independent replication (score capped at 1). The review only notes that vitamin B12 was NOT among the supplements showing benefit, providing weak negative evidence.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as a high-rigor design (score 2). However, the underlying claim is only a passing negative mention rather than a focused trial.', 'Vitamin B12 is named directly, but the claim concerns ''stress levels'' and ''anxiety in older women'' rather than anxiety as a clinical condition per se; the quote ''not folate or vitamin B12'' indicates B12 was excluded from beneficial findings. The condition match (anxiety) is loose given the stress-focused framing.', 'No mechanism for how vitamin B12 would or would not affect anxiety is asserted or evidenced in the claims. The claim is purely a negative observational result with no mechanistic basis given.', 'Only a single source is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed and is not penalized (n/a -> 1).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review in women found that vitamin B12 supplementation was not among the interventions that reduced stress/anxiety.', NULL, '{3deb4306-c62a-466a-af02-beb0699e4ee4}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:33.787760+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:33.787791+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('14227e5e-e4ad-4bd6-9e22-0fe60b684c61', '0e9fc7d0-5760-45f1-9649-1d440da1019c', 'fe554273-5290-4208-aa77-b23e067a334b', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review, which scores 1 (one synthesis is not independent replication). No additional independent studies are cited, so the maximum reserved for multiple consistent studies or a large RCT does not apply.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies for the highest rigor tier. However, the underlying study designs pooled within are not described in the claims.', 'Both the intervention (combined magnesium and vitamin B6) and the condition (premenstrual anxiety) are named directly in the verified claims, as in ''Combined magnesium and vitamin B6 supplementation reduced premenstrual anxiety.''', 'The claims state an effect on premenstrual anxiety but offer no mechanistic explanation of how magnesium and B6 act. No mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the quotes provided.', 'Claim 1 reports a benefit from combined supplementation while claim 2 notes no effect in isolation; these are not contradictory but describe a single review''s nuanced finding. With effectively one synthesis source, consistency cannot be independently assessed and defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that combined magnesium and vitamin B6 supplementation reduced premenstrual anxiety, though neither had an effect when used alone.', NULL, '{49015c83-c6ff-4dad-b021-44423dbd498f,1b0647ba-4322-4676-9df0-c4ab1e4693e0}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:37.006353+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:37.006385+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('cb8e76ba-2d5b-4fc0-9e01-97eebc87d266', '0e9fc7d0-5760-45f1-9649-1d440da1019c', '997ae490-b540-4e1e-ac1b-fbbac34448d3', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Both claims derive from a single systematic review, which counts as 1 (one synthesis, not independent replication). No additional independent primary studies or syntheses are cited, so a score of 2 is not warranted.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-rigor evidence (score 2). The review synthesizes supplementation effects on stress levels in women.', 'The claims explicitly name both magnesium and vitamin B6 in combination and reference premenstrual stress/anxiety, directly tying the intervention to a PMS-related outcome.', 'The claims state effectiveness in reducing premenstrual stress and anxiety but provide no mechanistic explanation for how magnesium and vitamin B6 act. No mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the quotes.', 'Both claims come from a single source and point in the same positive direction (reduced premenstrual stress and anxiety). With effectively one synthesis, consistency cannot be independently established, so it scores 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review suggests that magnesium combined with vitamin B6 may reduce premenstrual stress and anxiety.', NULL, '{b7250874-c833-40bf-91c2-fb78ec10f3da,d3da0128-8147-4356-8eec-df864a2a3030}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:39.286610+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:39.286623+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('1ebfd196-253e-4b84-872c-1c4f4b956399', '00ab920a-db04-48bf-9df9-eaca7bcc196b', '997ae490-b540-4e1e-ac1b-fbbac34448d3', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The on-topic PMS evidence comes from a single systematic review (claims 3-4) stating B6 up to 100 mg/day likely benefits premenstrual symptoms/depression. A single synthesis is not independent replication, so it scores 1; the other two claims concern anxiety in older women and are off-topic.', 'The relevant evidence (claims 3-4) derives from a systematic review of vitamin B-6 efficacy in PMS, which qualifies as high-tier design (meta-analysis/systematic review).', 'Claims 3-4 name both vitamin B-6 and premenstrual syndrome/symptoms directly, satisfying full drug-plus-condition specificity.', 'No mechanism is described in the claims; they only assert clinical benefit of B6 in premenstrual symptoms without any pathophysiological or biochemical explanation.', 'The on-topic PMS evidence is essentially a single systematic review with two consistent positive statements; with one source there is no independent cross-study agreement to assess, so this is scored neutral.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review concluded that vitamin B-6 doses up to 100 mg/day are likely beneficial in treating premenstrual symptoms and premenstrual depression.', NULL, '{b34a87c6-bdf0-41f8-99fe-3ab096dda192,cb89a5fe-db36-4dac-bcd4-bb7063ffeb95,a7f59bcf-1f8d-4d90-b91a-ef6e47bc4db7,ecd380b5-a01d-4b89-9472-4fd9c4af8b6f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:41.507072+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:41.507086+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('8e2162a1-bbed-4f18-8a8e-f665d9ad5054', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', 'fc6df098-33bb-45d7-a203-fdb0dc5095b1', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 2, 'Evidence comes from two systematic reviews (claims 1 and 2), but each is a single synthesis rather than independent replication; per scoring rules a single review scores 1. Two reviews likely overlap in the trials pooled and do not constitute three+ genuinely independent studies.', 'Both sources are systematic reviews of clinical trials (''systematic review of clinical trials'', ''a systematic review''), which qualify as rigor level 2.', 'One source explicitly names ''Vitex agnus castus for premenstrual syndrome and premenstrual dysphoric disorder,'' directly naming both the intervention and PMDD. The drug Vitex agnus-castus is clearly identified across both claims.', 'The claims address tolerability and adverse-event frequency only (''mild and generally infrequent'', ''well tolerated'') and provide no mechanism for the safety profile. No biological mechanism is asserted or evidenced.', 'Both reviews agree in direction, reporting that adverse events were mild/infrequent and that VAC was well tolerated. The two independent syntheses concur on favorable tolerability.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Two systematic reviews report that Vitex agnus-castus was well tolerated with mild and generally infrequent adverse events in women with PMS/PMDD.', NULL, '{bbaad3d0-d162-41af-a0e0-d335311d4dee,329d452e-27c5-43ff-a345-b34a5ce6140f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:44.729244+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:44.729285+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('3ac2ea32-9a23-4cbb-a6bd-4588c849d8b1', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', '997ae490-b540-4e1e-ac1b-fbbac34448d3', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of clinical trials (''Vitex agnus-castus extracts for female reproductive disorders: a systematic review of clinical trials''). A single synthesis is not independent replication, so this scores 1 rather than 2.', 'The source is a systematic review of clinical trials, which qualifies as high-tier study design under the rubric. No individual trial details (size, blinding) are provided in the claims, but a systematic review of clinical trials merits a 2.', 'The claim names both the intervention (Vitex extracts) and the condition (premenstrual syndrome) directly: ''benefits for Vitex extracts in the treatment of premenstrual syndrome.''', 'The verified claim asserts benefit but provides no mechanism of action for how Vitex agnus-castus affects PMS. No mechanistic detail is given, so plausibility cannot be scored above 0.', 'Only a single source/claim is available, with no breakdown of multiple independent studies'' directions of effect. Per the rubric, a single source defaults to 1 rather than being penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review of clinical trials reports benefits of Vitex agnus-castus extracts in treating premenstrual syndrome.', NULL, '{99f9f7e1-9036-4abd-9d9f-d798c77ab386}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:46.936159+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:46.936191+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c91cf43c-4400-43f0-b81a-c6215c6c3980', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', 'fc6df098-33bb-45d7-a203-fdb0dc5095b1', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 2, 'Evidence comes from two systematic reviews, but synthesis reviews are not independent replication—they likely pool overlapping trials. A single (or even two overlapping) systematic review is scored at most 1; neither describes a single large low-bias RCT specific to PMDD.', 'Both sources are systematic reviews of clinical trials, and one references eight studies positive for VAC in PMS/PMDD. Systematic reviews qualify for the highest design tier.', 'Both claims name Vitex agnus-castus (Vitex extracts/VAC) and PMDD explicitly. The drug and condition are both directly identified.', 'The claims assert efficacy benefits but provide no mechanism of action for how Vitex affects PMDD. No biological pathway is described or evidenced in the quotes.', 'One review states all eight studies were positive for VAC in PMS or PMDD, indicating consistent direction across multiple trials. The second review independently reports benefits, agreeing in direction.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Two systematic reviews report that Vitex agnus-castus extracts show benefit in treating PMDD, with one noting all eight included studies were positive.', NULL, '{673d8f80-34fc-438d-8275-1667b654f49f,c381f953-16bf-48da-9a7a-b5141ea58738}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:47.962659+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:47.962694+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('24c0740f-78c1-44bb-83e6-d89cdf32f9c1', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', '560e11c5-9e7c-4be7-8ac3-cce4bc35da18', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 2, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review of clinical trials, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules, a single systematic review scores 1, even though it pooled eight trials internally.', 'The source is a systematic review of clinical trials, which qualifies as rigor level 2. It summarizes controlled trials comparing Vitex against placebo and active comparators.', 'Both the intervention (Vitex agnus-castus extracts) and the condition (premenstrual syndrome) are named directly in the claims and quotes. The comparison outcomes specifically concern PMS.', 'The claims report only outcome superiority over placebo and comparators without any mechanistic explanation. No mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the verified claims.', 'Seven of eight trials found Vitex superior to placebo, and additional trials found it superior to pyridoxine and magnesium oxide. Results consistently agree in direction across multiple comparisons within the review.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review found Vitex agnus-castus extracts superior to placebo, pyridoxine, and magnesium oxide for premenstrual syndrome in most trials reviewed.', NULL, '{be431197-5aec-40e8-9a48-5c1af9c46077,b33dffd7-20ec-4048-b851-37b15f915f51,44c1f1fc-f975-48c6-9004-59f365c2b8a3}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:49.529501+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:49.529542+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('8c99c475-a635-4018-8a7e-ade3d97b4e7f', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', 'd5b98493-0b7f-4715-8283-4ea1b0210e3e', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 2, 2, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review of clinical trials, which by definition counts as one synthesis source, not independent replication. Per scoring rules a single systematic review scores 1; the trials pooled inside it do not count as independent sources.', 'The evidence comes from a systematic review of clinical trials, which qualifies as rigor level 2. The review explicitly compares Vitex to placebo and to active comparator bromocriptine.', 'Both the intervention (Vitex agnus-castus) and the condition (latent hyperprolactinaemia) are named directly in the claims, including specific outcomes such as TRH-stimulated prolactin secretion and luteal phase normalisation.', 'The mechanism is evidenced: claims show reduction of TRH-stimulated and serum prolactin and comparability to bromocriptine (a dopamine agonist), implicating a dopaminergic/prolactin-lowering pathway. Downstream effects on luteal phase, progesterone and oestradiol are measured biochemically, supporting an evidenced mechanism.', 'Multiple outcomes (prolactin reduction, luteal phase normalisation, progesterone and oestradiol increase, comparability to bromocriptine) all point in the same favourable direction. The review reports consistent superiority over placebo and equivalence to active comparator across endpoints.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Strong', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review of clinical trials found Vitex agnus-castus superior to placebo for reducing TRH-stimulated prolactin and normalising luteal-phase parameters, and comparable to bromocriptine for lowering serum prolactin in latent hyperprolactinaemia.', 'Vitex agnus-castus exerts dopaminergic activity that suppresses prolactin secretion, restoring luteal-phase progesterone and oestradiol, similar to the dopamine agonist bromocriptine.', '{4252b46c-a627-43e8-8249-3327ad513f92,c2c12781-c685-4003-8c30-d9c659bd9c7d,a56ca2bc-1d90-4db9-bc6a-bb525200bd61,6683164a-af25-4dfa-a1b1-6a690eaee616,d85c333b-9168-4b45-ad6e-5095c7dd5ef9,1b9b5bc6-0731-4cb6-8f23-b26987575f77}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:55.033194+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:55.033219+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('71e2c63d-b8ed-4541-8f2d-6670ed374b2b', 'dcd5ca46-ee57-4d35-b7e1-07b887d30b22', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The substantive efficacy data come from a single RCT (claims 2-10). The ''Medical management of endometriosis'' source (claims 11-12) merely references the same trial rather than providing independent corroboration. A single primary study scores 0.', 'The evidence is a randomized clinical trial comparing dienogest to a combined oral contraceptive (claims 1-2), which qualifies as RCT-level design. Outcomes include VAS scores, EHP-30 HRQoL, and validated B&B severity profiles.', 'Both the drug (dienogest, 2 mg/day) and the condition (endometriosis-associated pelvic pain) are named directly and repeatedly (claims 2, 4, 5).', 'No mechanism of action is described in any claim; the evidence is purely clinical-outcome based with no statement of how dienogest acts on endometriotic tissue or pain pathways.', 'Results derive essentially from one trial, so cross-study consistency cannot be assessed; within the trial, dienogest consistently improved VAS and HRQoL and was comparable to COC across multiple measures (claims 2, 6, 7-10).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'In a randomized trial of women with endometriosis, dienogest (2 mg/day) significantly improved endometriosis-associated pelvic pain (VAS mean difference 6.0, 95% CI 4.9-7.1) and HRQoL, comparable to a combined oral contraceptive.', NULL, '{5474cb5d-9894-4bcd-91fb-ebb8de512b5e,30c50baf-5936-4a90-818c-53e95b607ddd,5c9e7e77-bf93-46dc-be08-dd9450f6ec07,36589f10-0de7-4086-be84-0a0b722c510a,288d2851-6c53-4e3e-a475-041f0ce0a7fc,1ada2dce-fe50-4872-969f-8ff5ad220df2,b171a4d6-ea00-402b-91e7-0d128588ddb6,2a3be312-4e85-4cf1-9850-2870d7e0cf40,5d3bbb8b-8813-4bd2-b167-ec54cc40c63e,054cca5a-3d3d-46f5-a588-a548f8a4ec2f,9f74a569-7cff-4e1e-8a56-c4bd72f0cd4b,bc1b2eb7-5e26-46b6-8b2a-ab6031a13364}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:06:59.476911+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:06:59.476936+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('24568bf1-6566-48d6-863f-50af86c7ea34', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', '841239b7-f3ce-4e1c-841a-83b4d8df69e1', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review on VAC for PMS/PMDD, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules, a single systematic review scores 1, not 2.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-rigor design under the rubric. However, only a general safety conclusion is provided without specific trial-level data.', 'Both the intervention (Vitex agnus-castus/VAC extract) and the condition (PMS/PMDD) are named directly in the claim and quote.', 'The claim asserts safety but provides no mechanistic basis or explanation for why VAC is safe. No mechanism is described, so this is an unsupported assertion.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per the rubric, a single source is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review concluded that VAC extract is a safe alternative for treating PMS/PMDD symptoms.', NULL, '{3fe71136-a364-45d8-a424-c66b0d15dce7}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:02.703206+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:02.703248+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a0e085b4-e296-45a5-a680-5f170ce4dded', 'b03271a1-1ce3-49ea-b7b8-10c4ea4178c0', '841239b7-f3ce-4e1c-841a-83b4d8df69e1', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The single source is a systematic review, which counts as one synthesis (scored 1) rather than independent replication. No additional independent studies are cited, so the threshold for a score of 2 is not met.', 'The evidence derives from a systematic review (''Vitex agnus castus for premenstrual syndrome and premenstrual dysphoric disorder: a systematic review''), which qualifies for the highest rigor tier. No individual study design details are provided beyond the review-level synthesis.', 'Both the intervention (VAC extract / Vitex agnus-castus) and the condition (PMS/PMDD) are named directly in the verified claim and source title. The match is exact.', 'The claim only asserts efficacy (''safe and efficacious alternative'') without describing any biological mechanism. No mechanistic pathway is stated or evidenced in the provided claim.', 'Only one source/claim is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per the rule, a single source is scored 1 (not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review concluded that Vitex agnus-castus extract is a safe and efficacious option for treating PMS/PMDD symptoms.', NULL, '{250e1a14-fc77-4070-bf4c-cb792bd5a2ab}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:03.403579+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:03.403605+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('9a63b982-89ef-4e62-a8e8-e190fbe7aa95', '77ecea03-7ec4-437b-969a-2452a9574f70', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'The claims derive from a single randomized clinical trial (claims 1, 2) plus a review article restating that same trial''s content (claims 3, 4). This represents essentially one primary RCT, not multiple independent corroborating studies, so it scores at the low end.', 'The primary source is explicitly a ''Randomized clinical trial'' (claims 1, 2), which qualifies as RCT-level design. The accompanying review reinforces but does not add independent rigor.', 'Both the intervention (combined oral contraceptive) and the condition (endometriosis) are named directly and repeatedly in claims 1-4, including pain and HRQoL outcomes specific to endometriosis.', 'The claims assert COC improves endometriosis pain and quality of life but provide no explicit mechanistic detail (e.g., hormonal suppression of ectopic endometrial tissue). The mechanism is plausible but not evidenced in the quotes.', 'Evidence rests on a single trial with one review echoing it; there are no multiple independent studies to assess directional agreement, so consistency is scored as not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A randomized clinical trial found that combined oral contraceptives improved endometriosis-associated pain and health-related quality of life (EHP-30) in women with endometriosis.', 'Hormonal suppression by combined oral contraceptives may reduce endometriosis-associated pain, though the claims do not explicitly detail the mechanism.', '{6c4ca15c-0fcc-4a17-a1e2-22711fea8eab,25240d5e-1e96-47ed-b3ea-f95849980e1f,0f8e278e-f585-4aea-8afd-77e6bd512851,cf4f44a7-4fd9-4862-b1e7-aa9a2ba45322}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:03.526326+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:03.526354+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('47db524d-cd23-4794-8374-0aaa0e9a1bda', 'dcd5ca46-ee57-4d35-b7e1-07b887d30b22', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'safety', 'direct', 0, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Both claims derive from a single randomized clinical trial comparing dienogest vs combined oral contraceptives. A single primary study scores 0 for corroboration with no independent replication shown.', 'The source is explicitly a randomized clinical trial, which qualifies as high-rigor design. Both safety claims come from this RCT comparing dienogest to COC.', 'Both dienogest and endometriosis are named directly in the source title and claims regarding pain associated with endometriosis. The drug-condition pair is unambiguous.', 'The claims only assert that dienogest had fewer side-effects and a better safety/tolerability profile without describing any mechanism. No mechanistic explanation for the safety advantage is provided.', 'Both claims come from a single trial and point in the same direction (favorable safety vs COC), but there is no independent study to compare against. A single study is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'In a single randomized clinical trial of women with endometriosis, dienogest was associated with fewer side-effects and a better safety/tolerability profile than combined oral contraceptives.', NULL, '{aec00220-c6d0-46ef-b51b-a8f3ced2342b,8291a3c4-6365-4d9a-aadf-60e534756fe2}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:06.465242+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:06.465267+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('534c2656-c5dc-44e2-a9b5-a6fba9cadbed', '63952f1e-feff-4ffe-b250-3d621d2d84a8', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single primary RCT is cited (the dienogest vs COC trial). A single primary study scores 0 per the rubric; there is no independent replication or synthesis presented.', 'The source is explicitly a randomized clinical trial comparing dienogest vs COC for endometriosis pain, which qualifies as an RCT design scoring 2.', 'The claim names both combined oral contraceptives and endometriosis-associated pelvic pain directly, satisfying full specificity.', 'COCs suppress ovulation and reduce estrogen-driven endometrial proliferation, a plausible mechanism for reducing endometriosis pain, but no explicit mechanistic evidence is provided in the claims.', 'Only a single study is presented, so directional agreement cannot be assessed; per the rubric a single study is scored 1 and not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'In a single RCT, combined oral contraceptives significantly improved mean VAS pain scores for endometriosis-associated pelvic pain (4.54, 95% CI 3.1-5.9; p<0.0001).', 'COCs suppress ovulation and ovarian estrogen production, reducing estrogen-dependent endometrial lesion activity and associated pelvic pain.', '{402ffb88-59f2-4fd4-a732-03ceae7bc947}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:10.081583+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:10.081610+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('76da8e3e-3311-45c9-93ea-8f9648f968ae', '1205858f-dec0-465a-a27b-59f5b746fbac', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 0, 1, 'Only a single source is cited (one review/article on medical management of endometriosis), and it provides only a general assertion rather than corroborated trial data. A single non-synthesis source scores 0.', 'The claim derives from a narrative/management article asserting that nonhormonal treatment is ''vital,'' with no described RCT, meta-analysis, or quantitative outcome. This places it at observational/expert-statement level, not a rigorous controlled design.', 'Both the intervention (''nonhormonal treatment'') and the condition (''endometriosis'') are named directly in the quote and source title. The match is explicit.', 'The claim merely asserts nonhormonal treatment is vital in managing painful symptoms without describing any mechanism. No mechanistic pathway is provided or evidenced.', 'Only a single source is available, so direction of effect cannot be cross-compared. Per the rule, a single study is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single management article asserts that nonhormonal treatment is vital in managing painful symptoms of endometriosis, without supporting quantitative trial data.', NULL, '{fb8b1b21-6797-4394-9e6a-369dbdcffed1}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:10.849995+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:10.850028+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('b9d719f1-cdc2-42ca-97c5-b98222153e22', 'a17c87b5-12a9-4119-b7e9-bba5919d805b', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 0, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single source is cited, and the claim is a general assertion rather than a synthesis of independent studies. There is no evidence of multiple corroborating studies or a meta-analysis.', 'The single claim is a broad narrative statement (''is vital in managing painful symptoms'') from what appears to be a review/medical management article with no described study design, RCT, or quantitative data. This reads as expert opinion rather than rigorous trial evidence.', 'Both the intervention (hormonal treatment) and the condition (endometriosis) are named directly in the claim and source title (''Medical management of endometriosis''). The link is explicit.', 'Endometriosis is hormonally driven, so hormonal treatment to manage pain is mechanistically plausible. However, no specific mechanism is articulated or evidenced in the verified claim.', 'Only a single claim from a single source is provided, so consistency across studies cannot be assessed. Per scoring rules, a single source defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single review-level source asserts that hormonal treatment is vital for managing the painful symptoms of endometriosis, without quantitative data.', 'Endometriosis is an estrogen-dependent condition, so hormonal treatment may reduce pain by suppressing estrogen-driven lesion activity.', '{73c1bf5f-3926-49be-84a8-e464b97aa2e0}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:11.495605+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:11.495631+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c239161d-bbfa-4be3-af01-b18999b5a0ee', '4649c778-db16-4740-80c6-29a739610666', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 2, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review (''Use of aromatase inhibitors to treat endometriosis-related pain symptoms: a systematic review''). A single synthesis scores 1; the seven studies and three RCTs pooled inside it do not count as independent sources.', 'The evidence is a systematic review encompassing multiple studies, including three RCTs of post-operative therapy. Systematic reviews and RCTs are the highest design tier, justifying a score of 2.', 'Both the intervention (aromatase inhibitors) and the condition (endometriosis-related pain) are named directly and repeatedly in the claims and source title.', 'The claims assert efficacy in reducing pain but do not articulate the aromatase/estrogen-suppression mechanism. A plausible mechanism exists for endometriosis but is not spelled out in the quotes, so a score of 1 is appropriate.', 'Multiple claims from the review consistently point in the same direction: AIs (combined with progestogens or OCPs) reduce pain severity and improve quality of life. The review synthesizes seven studies and three RCTs with concordant positive findings.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Strong', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review (including three RCTs) found that aromatase inhibitors combined with progestogens or oral contraceptives reduce endometriosis-related pain severity and improve quality of life.', 'Aromatase inhibitors suppress local and systemic estrogen production, reducing estrogen-dependent endometriotic lesion activity and associated pain.', '{70285f36-02f6-4155-9087-87878dfaf3f3,64a929c0-bbe7-46fd-9c19-fda5caf5102d,a2d2e483-dec8-448c-bd02-fac4ca206d72,a82eb7b4-4695-43c8-b4b1-55f3cfd27757,b9612ec3-29f5-4376-8aff-c2af283cc44f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:15.097712+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:15.097731+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('81fa116c-4390-40af-a04d-a8ecf9d65de7', '98900338-61e9-49a6-9a91-0c479d3b0e47', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Both claims derive from a single systematic review (''Use of aromatase inhibitors to treat endometriosis-related pain symptoms: a systematic review''). A single synthesis scores 1 and is not independent replication; the trials pooled within it do not count as separate sources.', 'The evidence comes from a systematic review, which qualifies as the highest design tier under the rubric (meta-analysis/systematic review = 2).', 'The claims explicitly name letrozole combined with norethisterone acetate and endometriosis-related pain symptoms, so both the intervention and condition are directly identified.', 'Aromatase inhibitors like letrozole reduce local estrogen production driving endometriotic lesions, a plausible mechanism, but the claims themselves only assert improved pain outcomes without spelling out or evidencing the mechanism.', 'Both claims come from the same single review and concern related pain endpoints in the same direction; with effectively one source there is no independent corroboration to assess, so consistency defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that letrozole combined with norethisterone acetate reduces endometriosis-related pain and deep dyspareunia more than norethisterone acetate alone.', 'Letrozole, an aromatase inhibitor, lowers local estrogen production that sustains endometriotic lesions, potentially enhancing the analgesic effect of progestin therapy.', '{ee9cab52-f4a5-4187-90bc-21951ff6f59d,1959f8eb-5c3f-4d7a-ac03-3926a9f389db}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:18.635580+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:18.635607+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('91a78aff-f89e-43ed-970f-abeb892ea9da', '3b89967a-200f-4a6c-8121-63e623f824ab', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'safety', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 0, 1, 'Only a single source is cited, describing two-year efficacy and safety data of relugolix combination therapy in women with endometriosis-associated pain. A single primary study scores 0; there is no independent corroboration from multiple studies.', 'The claim references two-year safety data but does not specify study design (e.g., RCT, extension trial). Without explicit confirmation of an RCT or meta-analysis, the evidence is treated conservatively as a single trial-level report.', 'Both the intervention (relugolix combination therapy) and condition (endometriosis-associated pain in women) are named directly in the quote.', 'The claim only asserts that safety data exist; no mechanism for any safety effect is described or evidenced in the provided claim.', 'Only a single source is available, so directional consistency cannot be evaluated and is not penalized per the single-study rule.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Two-year safety data exist for relugolix combination therapy in women with endometriosis-associated pain, though no specific safety findings are quantified in the verified claim.', NULL, '{2f1674f7-80fa-4052-924e-1c8083c93558}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:18.727279+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:18.727314+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('22ceafec-8113-40d7-9804-f7e29c178d82', '3b89967a-200f-4a6c-8121-63e623f824ab', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Two claims appear to derive from a review/management article citing relugolix combination therapy trials, but no independent replication or large low-bias RCT is verified here. The evidence reflects single-source descriptions rather than multiple independent consistent studies.', 'Claims describe placebo-controlled comparisons and two-year efficacy data suggestive of RCT-derived evidence, but the source is a management/review article and study design is not explicitly confirmed as RCT. Conservatively scored at observational/small trial level given limited detail.', 'Both claims name relugolix combination therapy directly and endometriosis/endometriosis-associated pain explicitly. The drug and condition are both clearly identified.', 'Relugolix is a GnRH antagonist plausibly reducing endometriosis-associated pain via estrogen suppression, but the claims do not explicitly state or evidence this mechanism. Mechanism is plausible but not detailed in the quotes.', 'The two claims both point toward a positive effect on endometriosis-associated pain (short-term vs placebo and two-year efficacy), but they are not independent studies allowing a directional consistency assessment. Treated as effectively single-source, scored neutral.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'Relugolix combination therapy is described as having an effect on endometriosis-associated pain versus placebo with reported two-year efficacy in women.', 'As a GnRH receptor antagonist combination therapy, relugolix likely suppresses ovarian estrogen production, reducing endometriosis-associated pain.', '{11a859b9-085b-4ebd-af92-2025844614f4,b0150766-febc-4d13-8ff6-bf32183b3f25}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:20.421916+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:20.421946+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('08d977aa-931c-453b-92ca-4bafe35b8396', 'f3581d69-d2a6-473e-b1f9-0043946c59c9', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'The evidence derives from a single systematic review (one synthesis), which per scoring rules counts as 1, not independent replication. No additional independent studies are cited in the claims.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as the high-rigor tier. The claim describes a comparative postsurgical regimen evaluating recurrence reduction.', 'The claim names both the intervention (AIs combined with GnRH analogue) and the condition (endometriosis/recurrence) directly. The comparison to GnRH analogue alone is explicit.', 'The combination plausibly reduces recurrence by suppressing estrogen via both ovarian and local aromatase inhibition, but the claim only asserts an outcome without detailing a mechanism. Thus mechanism is plausible but not evidenced in the quote.', 'Only a single systematic review is presented, so direction cannot be cross-checked against independent sources. Per the rule, a single source is scored 1 and not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that 6 months of aromatase inhibitors plus a GnRH analogue after surgery reduces endometriosis recurrence risk compared with GnRH analogue alone.', 'Adding aromatase inhibitors to GnRH analogue further suppresses local and peripheral estrogen production, reducing residual endometriotic lesion stimulation and recurrence.', '{2cdd7d8e-81b9-402d-a7ae-d81aba5676d2}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:23.802688+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:23.802722+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('ae867172-c1c7-4473-b252-0e9ecc283d74', '865928ab-5cd9-451e-af91-5635dccdee68', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review (''Use of aromatase inhibitors to treat endometriosis-related pain symptoms: a systematic review''). A single synthesis is not independent replication, so the maximum score is 1; no additional independent sources are provided.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as a high-rigor design under the rubric. However, the underlying trial designs pooled within it are not described in the claims.', 'Both the intervention (letrozole + norethisterone acetate) and the condition (endometriosis-related pain) are named directly in the claims and source title. The comparison is explicitly within the endometriosis treatment context.', 'The claims report a lower incidence of adverse effects and lower discontinuation versus letrozole+triptorelin, but provide no mechanistic explanation for this safety/tolerability difference. No mechanism is asserted or evidenced.', 'The two claims (lower adverse effect incidence and lower discontinuation rate) agree in direction, both favoring better tolerability of the norethisterone acetate combination. However, they derive from a single review rather than multiple independent studies, so consistency cannot be robustly established.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review reports that letrozole combined with norethisterone acetate causes fewer adverse effects and a lower discontinuation rate than letrozole combined with triptorelin in treating endometriosis-related pain.', NULL, '{1c432fae-bfce-4007-82d3-2d0e6c3d093d,42d0cf71-d12e-4061-88ce-00856b5e753f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:26.621382+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:26.621406+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('de3d1786-d79a-43db-bb33-d8ac4d874519', '97cc587b-f617-4589-b1df-9139f8a7ca7d', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence derives from a single systematic review of aromatase inhibitors for endometriosis-related pain. A single synthesis counts as 1, not independent replication; only one source and one claim are provided.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-design rigor (score 2). However, no details on pooled study designs or quality are given in the claim.', 'Both the drug (letrozole) and the condition (endometriosis) are named directly in the claim and source title. The claim explicitly addresses adverse effects in endometriosis treatment.', 'The claim asserts a higher incidence of adverse effects but provides no mechanism for why letrozole causes them. No physiological pathway is described.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per the rule, a single source defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that letrozole is associated with a higher incidence of adverse effects when used for endometriosis-related pain.', NULL, '{95c9af70-97cc-4b10-85df-0840ff294083}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:26.641163+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:26.641194+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('9866ddcf-513d-4584-84a4-59060ee37c03', '97cc587b-f617-4589-b1df-9139f8a7ca7d', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The evidence comes from a single systematic review (''Use of aromatase inhibitors to treat endometriosis-related pain symptoms: a systematic review''). Per scoring rules, a single systematic review scores 1 and does not constitute independent replication. No additional independent sources are presented.', 'The source is a systematic review of aromatase inhibitors for endometriosis-related pain, which qualifies as high-rigor design. However, the underlying study quality of pooled trials is not described in the claims.', 'Both the intervention (letrozole, an aromatase inhibitor) and the condition (endometriosis-related pain) are directly named in the claims and source title. The claims specifically discuss letrozole''s effects in endometriosis.', 'The claims report null efficacy findings (no improvement in satisfaction, no influence on recurrence) without describing any mechanism of action. No mechanistic basis is asserted or evidenced in the verified claims.', 'Both claims derive from the same single systematic review and report consistent null findings (no benefit on satisfaction or recurrence). With only one source, directional consistency across independent studies cannot be assessed, so this scores 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review found that letrozole does not improve patient satisfaction or influence symptom recurrence after discontinuation in endometriosis-related pain.', NULL, '{f7dde77e-07ae-490e-aff8-efce11b92f0d,1be2529e-2f11-4775-be28-dca2311ce6c6}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:28.010405+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:28.010429+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('f1141f10-e001-4cce-85a4-f40f53ba72cf', '619d4a83-bc1f-4359-84e2-1ce529ca51e8', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Only a single pilot study is referenced, which is explicitly preliminary and calls for ''further investigation.'' A single small primary study scores 0 for independent corroboration.', 'The source is described as a pilot study, which is a small trial. Pilot studies provide weak rigor and score 1 at most.', 'The condition (endometriosis) is named directly, but the intervention is given as ''unspecified treatment'' in the claim (''This treatment''), though the source title mentions letrozole. The drug is not clearly named within the verified claim itself, limiting specificity.', 'The single verified claim only asserts the treatment is ''promising'' without describing any mechanism of action. No mechanistic basis is evidenced or even stated.', 'Only one study is present, so directional consistency cannot be assessed across sources. Per the n/a rule, this scores 1 and is not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single pilot study suggests a treatment for endometriosis-related pain symptoms is promising but warrants further investigation.', NULL, '{f197756a-1fb2-4193-9e77-c90b05bc8332}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:30.917408+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:30.917433+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('cd3357af-4f2f-4ce7-a536-5279cd4873b4', '9ec0dee5-cd94-438e-b8b2-deef0bfa5e49', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review covering curcumin, quercetin, and resveratrol. A single synthesis scores 1 and does not constitute independent replication of quercetin-specific findings.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as a high-rigor design (meta-analysis/review tier). However, the underlying studies pooled are not described in the claim.', 'Both quercetin and endometriosis are named directly in the claim and quote (''quercetin... potential application in the endometriosis treatment'').', 'The claim only asserts ''beneficial effects'' and ''potential application'' without describing any mechanism by which quercetin acts on endometriosis pathophysiology.', 'Only a single source (systematic review) is provided, so directional agreement across independent sources cannot be assessed; scored as n/a per the rule.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reported that quercetin showed beneficial effects suggesting potential application in endometriosis treatment.', NULL, '{44331c23-b42f-4def-a159-3c46b9b79093}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:34.715181+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:34.715219+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c1a9fcc6-d1ea-4139-b7f9-d39660bcf57d', 'ebc40b77-b7eb-433a-aef9-4bbf35afb4bb', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 0, 'Evidence comes from a systematic review/meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines (claims 1-3), which counts as a single synthesis (score 1, not independent replication). Claim 4 is from a separate review but is non-quantitative; the dominant high-quality source is one meta-analysis.', 'The primary source is a systematic review and meta-analysis (claims 1-3) used to inform international evidence-based guidelines, which qualifies as the highest rigor tier. Claim 4 is from a comparison/review article.', 'Both inositol and PCOS are named directly in all claims (e.g., ''inositol in the management of PCOS''). The intervention and condition are unambiguous.', 'Claim 4 asserts inositol counters ''the endocrine-metabolic disorders'' of PCOS, implying an insulin-sensitizing/metabolic mechanism, but this is asserted rather than mechanistically evidenced in the quotes. No molecular mechanism data is presented.', 'The sources directly conflict: the meta-analysis finds efficacy ''indeterminate,'' ''limited and inconclusive,'' and ''may have no effect'' (claims 1-3), while claim 4 calls inositol ''useful.'' Results disagree in direction.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review/meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines found the evidence for inositol in PCOS limited and inconclusive, with efficacy indeterminate, though one comparison review described it as useful for endocrine-metabolic disorders.', 'Inositol may act as an insulin sensitizer to counter the endocrine-metabolic disturbances of PCOS.', '{5bc141b8-0c4f-4ed7-88ef-b7edb9416bb0,fc13afc3-b57c-48e1-9c04-04c72b8367d9,4c33a5f3-78d7-4cdf-8196-e92fa0afac3c,26394d1d-e42c-45ea-bcf1-bd203824acaf}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:35.274574+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:35.274603+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('d94b767a-301b-4232-80a6-1218fe8ff6da', 'db078ae7-eba6-47b4-bb00-3c5cfb87fab6', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review ("Impact of curcumin, quercetin, or resveratrol... A systematic review"). A single synthesis scores 1 and is not independent replication; the pooled trials inside it do not count as independent sources.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as a higher-rigor design (meta-analysis/systematic review = 2). However, the review covers preclinical/mechanistic studies, which tempers the practical weight of the score.', 'Both the intervention (curcumin) and the condition (endometriosis) are named directly in the claim and quote: "potential application in the endometriosis treatment." The specificity is clear.', 'The claim asserts beneficial effects on the pathophysiology of endometriosis but does not detail an evidenced mechanism in the provided quote. This supports plausibility but not a fully evidenced mechanistic chain.', 'Only a single source (one systematic review) is provided, so directional agreement across independent studies cannot be assessed. Per rubric, a single source defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review reports that curcumin shows beneficial effects on endometriosis pathophysiology, indicating potential therapeutic application.', 'Curcumin may favorably modulate the pathophysiology of endometriosis, though the specific mechanism is not detailed in the provided claim.', '{65b91787-b6c7-45b5-9a2f-3ba91648502a}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:36.301409+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:36.301425+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('3c7c4a77-e799-4a04-b3af-d89bf98b4be5', 'dee6bfca-af95-44bc-b5ff-ec22124400be', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'The evidence comes from a single systematic review of resveratrol''s effects on endometriosis. Per scoring rules, a single synthesis counts as 1, not independent replication. Only one claim/source is shown.', 'The source is a systematic review (''Impact of curcumin, quercetin, or resveratrol on the pathophysiology of endometriosis: A systematic review''), which qualifies as rigor level 2 by design.', 'Both the intervention (resveratrol) and the condition (endometriosis) are named directly in the claim and the source title. The match is explicit.', 'The claim asserts beneficial effects on endometriosis pathophysiology but the verified text does not detail a specific evidenced mechanism. A plausible mechanism is implied through ''pathophysiology'' framing without molecular detail provided.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so directional agreement across independent studies cannot be assessed. Per rules, a single source is scored 1 (not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reported that resveratrol showed beneficial effects suggesting potential application in endometriosis treatment.', 'Resveratrol may favorably modulate the pathophysiology of endometriosis, though the specific molecular mechanism is not detailed in the verified claim.', '{92a3a7dd-b2ed-4bf1-a642-643312e2bdbe}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:38.991057+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:38.991086+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('09fe01d8-657f-40d4-b4f5-394bacdab9e7', '2b3bca80-a383-4326-94e2-1694787c8bff', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single pilot study, and a pilot study is by definition small and underpowered. A single primary study scores 0 for corroboration; there is no independent replication.', 'The source is described as a pilot study, indicating a small trial rather than a large, well-powered RCT. Small trials score 1 on the design dimension.', 'The claim directly names laparoscopic excision plus oral contraceptives and endometriosis-related pelvic pain, satisfying both the drug/intervention and condition naming requirements.', 'The combination of surgical excision plus hormonal suppression is mechanistically plausible for reducing endometriosis pain, but the claims assert pain reduction without detailing or evidencing the mechanism. Hence plausible but not explicitly evidenced.', 'Only a single study is provided, so directional agreement across sources cannot be assessed and is scored as n/a (1). The single study consistently shows decreasing pain over time.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'In a single pilot study, laparoscopic excision plus oral contraceptives significantly reduced chronic pelvic pain intensity in endometriosis patients compared with 6-month follow-up and baseline.', 'Surgical removal of endometriotic lesions combined with hormonal suppression of estrogen-driven lesion activity reduces endometriosis-related pelvic pain.', '{8559bee1-8f15-420a-b1f4-cc0eb563e953}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:42.486692+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:42.486717+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('731b696e-298c-4d0b-b495-5da451ccb5ac', '392dccb2-3967-4f6c-b23c-3c4095a14b99', '13c33c1b-98d6-4ef0-bb1a-add1344261a5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'All three claims derive from a single source, described in its own title as a ''pilot study.'' There is no independent replication, and a single small primary study scores 0.', 'The source is a pilot study comparing letrozole plus OCs versus OCs alone, indicating a small comparative trial rather than a large RCT or meta-analysis. Small trial/pilot design merits a score of 1.', 'Both the intervention (oral contraceptives) and condition (endometriosis-related pain) are named directly in the claims and source title, with specific outcomes (chronic pelvic pain, deep dyspareunia).', 'Oral contraceptives plausibly reduce endometriosis pain by suppressing ovarian hormonal stimulation of ectopic endometrial tissue, but the claims report only clinical outcomes (pain scores) and do not present mechanistic evidence, so the mechanism is plausible but not evidenced here.', 'Evidence comes from a single study, so direction of effect cannot be cross-checked against independent sources; per the n/a rule a single study is scored 1. Within the study, pain and dyspareunia outcomes are consistently positive.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'In a single pilot study, oral contraceptives alone significantly reduced chronic pelvic pain and deep dyspareunia in endometriosis patients during and after treatment.', 'Oral contraceptives suppress cyclical ovarian hormonal stimulation of ectopic endometrial tissue, reducing endometriosis-related pain.', '{8f34e9aa-7434-4e25-97ad-a28e61730684,8037973d-8f21-4859-baa3-51f25391840f,05711879-380d-4ed4-ac4c-6697c21b9996}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:43.972301+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:43.972333+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('3afe719e-4d18-42ba-b498-fe39c796ca3c', 'e8223fc1-98e9-4dc4-80b8-fdcc5012a54c', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 2, 2, 2, 1, 2, 'Evidence comes from multiple independent sources, including a systematic review and meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines (claim 1), plus separate primary studies in teenagers (claims 2-5) and overweight patients (claims 6-10). The consistency across a synthesis and independent trials supports a high corroboration score.', 'Claim 1 is from a systematic review and meta-analysis, the highest tier of evidence here. The other sources are comparative treatment studies, and the meta-analysis anchors strong rigor.', 'Multiple claims name both myo-inositol and PCOS directly (e.g., ''Inositol for Polycystic Ovary Syndrome'' and ''treatment of patients with PCOS''). Both intervention and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The claims report improvements in insulin resistance and metabolic parameters (claims 9, 10), implying an insulin-sensitizing mechanism, but no explicit mechanistic pathway is described. The effect is plausible but only asserted, not mechanistically evidenced.', 'Results consistently point in a positive direction across sources: metabolic improvements in the meta-analysis (claim 1), weight/BMI reductions in teenagers (claims 2-3), and menstrual, endocrine, and insulin-resistance improvements in patients (claims 7-10). No contradictory findings appear.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Strong', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A guideline-informing systematic review and meta-analysis plus independent studies indicate myo-inositol improves metabolic measures, menstrual regularity, and insulin resistance in PCOS patients.', 'Myo-inositol may act as an insulin-sensitizing agent, improving insulin resistance and associated endocrine/metabolic parameters in PCOS.', '{fb3d9ec2-e0f5-4b21-b49d-97c01d29b3ea,b47c855f-5a5b-43db-bc61-7bb21bdb3098,ccf97769-2a80-4511-94a7-34bd17e3c750,5e61dd95-9ad6-40ff-bb1f-8bf0576a105b,c06fa473-0861-4ffb-9aba-8742ef399774,aaf136ef-7988-4cdb-8887-7c14b050f205,89fcc520-277b-4189-a187-b95f04f55148,1a28fbe2-8ea1-4eaf-ab1a-16610c614caa,ee6d5804-0b92-405c-b3ad-e45b7ce2b46d,fffd6a34-e351-46c8-8b7f-7bfb4138e308}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:45.959751+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:45.959780+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('26803be8-4a95-4993-836f-6adec6e7ff78', 'e8223fc1-98e9-4dc4-80b8-fdcc5012a54c', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines. A single synthesis scores 1, not 2, because pooled trials within one review do not constitute independent replication.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis, which is a high-rigor design (score 2). It was conducted to inform an evidence-based guideline update.', 'The claim names both myo-inositol and PCOS directly, addressing a specific safety outcome (gastrointestinal adverse events) compared to metformin.', 'The claim asserts fewer GI adverse events but provides no mechanistic explanation for why myo-inositol is better tolerated than metformin. No mechanism is described.', 'Only a single meta-analysis is provided, so directional consistency across independent studies cannot be assessed (n/a, scored 1). The single source reports a consistent direction favoring myo-inositol.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis found that myo-inositol likely causes fewer gastrointestinal adverse events than metformin in women with PCOS.', NULL, '{b8714ef9-d3c3-41a3-8096-0dc761a6d71d}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:50.239575+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:50.239604+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('c0d9e7a1-ca6e-4f0f-8407-d494ffb01464', '43e6f623-ab3a-47ea-9f8a-05a39ba84a4d', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines, which scores 1 (one synthesis is not independent replication). No additional independent sources are provided.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis, which qualifies as high-rigor design (score 2).', 'The claim names metformin specifically and concerns PCOS directly, with the source being a PCOS guideline review. Both drug and condition are named.', 'The claim that GI adverse events are mild and self-limited is consistent with metformin''s known GI tolerability profile, a plausible characterization but no detailed mechanism is evidenced in the quote.', 'Only a single source is provided, so directional consistency across studies cannot be assessed and is scored as n/a (1).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', true, 1, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines reports that metformin-related gastrointestinal adverse events in PCOS are typically mild and self-limited.', NULL, '{6ff7653d-e99f-4293-89ab-3885b7c54e2c}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:50.814240+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:50.814269+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('95acd5b2-2151-4a24-b6ab-b81144fabfd7', 'a8d2f9d5-2557-4e41-9da2-5c688edf935a', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 2, 2, 2, 1, 2, 'Evidence comes from two distinct sources: a systematic review and meta-analysis informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines, plus a separate comparative treatment study, both showing consistent metabolic and ovulatory/menstrual benefits. The presence of a meta-analysis plus an independent primary study supports a score of 2.', 'One source is a systematic review and meta-analysis (the Inositol for PCOS guideline update), which is high-rigor design. The comparative MI vs DCI treatment study adds trial-level data.', 'Both D-chiro-inositol and PCOS are named directly in all claims (e.g., ''D-chiro-inositol (DCI) for some metabolic measures'' in PCOS patients).', 'Claims reference improvements in insulin resistance and endocrine/metabolic parameters, implying an insulin-sensitizing mechanism, but no explicit mechanistic pathway is detailed in the quotes. Mechanism is plausible but only asserted via outcome measures.', 'Both sources agree in direction: DCI improves metabolic measures, ovulation/menstrual regularity, and insulin resistance. The meta-analysis and the comparative study point the same way.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Strong', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review/meta-analysis and a comparative treatment study indicate D-chiro-inositol provides benefits for some metabolic measures, ovulation, menstrual regularity, and insulin resistance in PCOS patients.', 'D-chiro-inositol likely acts as an insulin sensitizer, improving insulin resistance and consequently endocrine and ovulatory function in PCOS.', '{495277ed-c6db-45fd-8de9-b6368e2c891b,5abc662c-d47c-40a4-8641-aa329e2f5333,6a8001c6-180e-44e1-b61c-ea6bded278bb,72ad9833-d2a1-46be-88bc-d9de4e1432e4,493e2a3c-a9e0-43b9-87d3-2419682208c6,fe9bbe1d-5b7c-4097-9c0a-b25cc54da64e}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:51.277230+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:51.277260+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('b3fb77b7-719c-4914-9092-7070c89cd723', '43e6f623-ab3a-47ea-9f8a-05a39ba84a4d', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from two systematic reviews/meta-analyses (one on inositol comparisons, one on COCP comparisons), each a single synthesis rather than independent replication of the same comparison. No single large low-bias RCT is described, so this stays at 1.', 'Both sources are systematic reviews and meta-analyses informing the 2023 international PCOS guidelines, which is the highest design tier. Claims 6-8 report pooled effect estimates with confidence intervals.', 'Both metformin and PCOS are named directly throughout (e.g., ''Metformin may improve waist-hip ratio and hirsutism'' in PCOS, and ''Metformin and Combined Oral Contraceptive Pills in the Management of Polycystic Ovary Syndrome''). The drug and condition are unambiguous.', 'Metformin''s insulin-sensitizing action plausibly underlies improvements in waist-hip ratio and androgen-related outcomes, but no explicit mechanistic statement is given in the claims. Mechanism is plausible but only implied, not evidenced here.', 'Results are mixed and comparator-dependent: metformin appears better than inositol for waist-hip ratio and hirsutism but inferior to COCP on FAI, SHBG, and testosterone. The directions differ across comparisons rather than agreeing, so consistency is not strong.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', true, 1, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'In meta-analyses informing the 2023 PCOS guidelines, metformin may improve waist-hip ratio and hirsutism versus inositol but is inferior to combined oral contraceptives on androgen markers (FAI, SHBG, testosterone) in women with PCOS.', 'Metformin''s insulin-sensitizing effects may reduce hyperandrogenism and central adiposity in PCOS, though it is less effective than COCP at lowering androgen indices.', '{91baf067-087b-46ac-86bf-a6d14d35b04c,8abd240a-905c-4f53-8a79-777e53ecc364,6536f474-181b-405f-be06-f2e6c7a1cf9c,a7168e80-7026-4127-b62b-ba5b3eb7d32d,bebaf9c7-ee37-4679-acaa-ca8c9b7ad3db,df5bc342-db37-41f6-b8a8-81d8224fd785,18278acd-994c-4783-9b11-5421514b1574,2ff256ef-1dae-40de-927d-e0d0a9459694}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:56.547985+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:56.548013+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('57c339d2-6a20-42a9-a6ca-2029531b67ee', '7c7df97c-9f1a-4a3c-95f0-455dd721c49d', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review and meta-analysis (Metformin and COCP in PCOS). A single synthesis scores 1, not 2, as the pooled trials within it do not count as independent replication.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis, which scores 2 on study design. It reports pooled effect estimates with confidence intervals for insulin and insulin resistance.', 'Both the intervention (COCP) and the condition (PCOS) are named directly in the source title and claims, with comparisons to metformin and combination treatment.', 'The claims report comparative outcomes (insulin, insulin resistance, hirsutism) but assert no mechanism by which COCP affects these PCOS parameters. No mechanistic explanation is provided in the quotes.', 'Results come from a single meta-analytic source, so cross-study consistency cannot be independently assessed. The findings within it are coherent: COCP inferior on insulin metrics but equivalent on hirsutism.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis found COCP was inferior to combination treatment for insulin and insulin resistance in PCOS, but showed no difference in hirsutism versus metformin or combination treatment.', NULL, '{beb640dd-966f-4f9b-b354-2508e682f2f9,6e53b0d1-945d-4420-9c2a-9dd123f7cd86,1719e022-26fd-4aec-8905-631646e8778d,b652b818-3180-4b11-b27c-16fa50c4db03}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:57.738946+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:57.738976+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('f935cbb3-c3cb-4b1c-90fd-3cae8214121b', '19b15ca6-ae62-440c-a151-0c3a69190217', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'The single source is a systematic review and meta-analysis, which per the rubric scores 1 as one synthesis (not independent replication). No additional independent sources are provided.', 'The source is explicitly a systematic review and meta-analysis, which qualifies as the highest rigor tier (2) in the rubric.', 'The claim directly names both the intervention (metformin and COCP) and the condition (PCOS), addressing efficacy targeting hyperinsulinemia and hyperandrogenism.', 'The claim asserts a mechanism—targeting hyperinsulinemia and hyperandrogenism, the two major endocrine disturbances of PCOS—which is plausible but the quote describes biochemical benefits without detailed mechanistic evidence beyond the asserted endocrine targets.', 'Only a single synthesis source is provided, with no comparison across multiple independent studies in these claims, so consistency cannot be assessed and is scored neutrally per the rubric.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis reports that combined metformin and COCP treatment provides some biochemical benefits by targeting both hyperinsulinemia and hyperandrogenism in PCOS.', 'Combining metformin (improving insulin sensitivity/hyperinsulinemia) with COCP (reducing hyperandrogenism) addresses both major endocrine disturbances of PCOS.', '{5130f015-850b-4372-8866-e7f479da2fdf}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:58.895845+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:58.895875+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('d9cd8f9c-6ae4-4173-8185-df804788b214', 'fcf54880-cd97-4795-b81a-7025aa1c62ef', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review and meta-analysis comparing COCP with combination treatment in PCOS. A single synthesis scores 1 — the trials pooled inside are not counted as independent sources.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis, which qualifies as high-rigor design. Claims report pooled effect estimates with confidence intervals.', 'Both COCP and PCOS are named directly in the source title and claims, with specific outcomes (FAI, SHBG, testosterone).', 'COCP affects androgen-related markers like SHBG and FAI, a plausible hormonal mechanism, but the claims do not explicitly explain or evidence the mechanism beyond reporting outcomes.', 'Results come from a single meta-analysis source; comparisons are internally consistent (COCP inferior on FAI and SHBG, no difference in testosterone), but there is no independent replication to assess cross-source agreement.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis found COCP inferior to combination treatment for FAI and SHBG in PCOS, with no difference in testosterone.', 'COCP modulates androgen activity via effects on SHBG and free androgen index in PCOS.', '{d0a670b7-fcf6-4a1f-bdc2-34dc62bf1648,4cd3e7ec-1251-4054-bbb5-2e20195a1fda,68e83450-e0ac-4fd2-a7e2-0bc473d7ff41}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:07:59.482575+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:07:59.482678+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('11a9e493-6261-4266-9bb2-b0a0c60f9fcb', '4563b459-fda9-4b9b-b78b-8bcfc7bb67b2', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Only a single primary study (a follow-up comparison) is cited, with no independent replication. A single primary study scores 0.', 'The source is a follow-up comparison study, which reads as an observational or small comparative trial rather than a large RCT or meta-analysis. This warrants a rigor score of 1.', 'PCOS is named directly, but the intervention is described only as ''this natural compound,'' with the source title mentioning Myo-Inositol. The drug is not explicitly named in the claim itself, so specificity is partial.', 'The claim asserts improvement in metabolic and hormonal parameters but provides no mechanistic explanation for how the compound achieves these effects. Mechanism is at best asserted, not described.', 'Only a single study/claim is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per the rule, a single study is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single follow-up comparison study suggests myo-inositol alone improves metabolic and hormonal parameters in PCOS adolescents.', NULL, '{00b42ad5-81da-4220-ab0f-b333486a493b}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:03.125406+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:03.125435+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('6cf7dc4d-62fe-4e3a-b93e-bdcc398bccac', '8ca4776e-e536-4d53-a526-78596f65cc35', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'Only a single primary study (a follow-up comparison) is cited, with no independent replication. A single primary study scores 0 by definition.', 'The source is a follow-up comparison study, which appears to be a small comparative/observational trial in adolescents rather than a large RCT or meta-analysis. This corresponds to observational/small-trial rigor.', 'The claim names both the intervention (natural compound—Myo-Inositol—combined with OCP) and the condition (PCOS) directly. The source title confirms PCOS teenagers and the specific therapies.', 'The claim asserts improvement of metabolic and hormonal parameters, which is mechanistically plausible for inositol/OCP therapy in PCOS, but no explicit mechanism is detailed or evidenced in the quote. Thus plausible but not evidenced.', 'Only one study is presented, so directional consistency across sources cannot be assessed. Per rules, a single study is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single follow-up comparison study suggests that a natural compound (Myo-Inositol) combined with OCP improves metabolic and hormonal parameters in PCOS adolescents.', NULL, '{593d1e53-943c-4eb8-b322-7876628fbe44}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:05.863174+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:05.863209+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('8e50449f-e579-43fa-967a-3d94dd72a1d4', '23563087-0014-4122-a438-e512c99d3f7b', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 0, 1, 'Only a single source is provided, and the verified claim offers no indication of multiple independent studies or a meta-analysis. A single source making a general therapeutic recommendation cannot establish independent corroboration.', 'The source title suggests a comparative study (Myo-inositol vs. D-chiro inositol), but no study design, sample size, or RCT details are provided in the claim. Without explicit evidence of an RCT or meta-analysis, this can only be scored as observational/small-trial level.', 'Both the intervention (D-chiro inositol) and the condition (PCOS) are named directly in the verified claim and quote. The match is explicit and unambiguous.', 'The claim asserts therapeutic potential but provides no mechanistic explanation for how D-chiro inositol acts on PCOS. No insulin-sensitizing or other pathway is described in the verified claims.', 'Only a single source/claim is available, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per the n/a rule, this is scored 1 rather than penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single source proposes D-chiro inositol as a potentially valid therapeutic approach for treating patients with PCOS.', NULL, '{9420e353-d70b-4d70-aa8e-1ba791c60e39}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:07.165606+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:07.165628+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('d60ccbca-3bfc-4994-a7c7-627ef7b71346', 'fadba698-8ddc-4feb-9951-9d03a051cd6f', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 2, 1, 1, 'All four claims derive from a single primary study on lean PCOS teenagers. There is no independent corroboration from additional studies, so this scores at the bottom of the single-primary-study range.', 'The source is a follow-up comparison study in a small population of teenagers (ages 17-19), consistent with a small comparative trial rather than a large RCT or meta-analysis. No randomization, blinding, or sample size is described, so this is observational/small-trial level.', 'Both the intervention (myo-inositol combined with OCP) and the condition (PCOS) are named directly in the claims and source title. The specificity is unambiguous.', 'The claims assert improvements in metabolic and hormonal parameters, which is mechanistically plausible since myo-inositol is an insulin-sensitizing agent relevant to PCOS pathophysiology. However, no explicit mechanistic pathway is evidenced in the quotes, so this is plausible but not evidenced.', 'All claims come from a single study, so cross-study consistency cannot be assessed. Per the n/a rule, this is scored 1 and not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Emerging', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'In a single small follow-up study of lean PCOS teenagers, myo-inositol combined with oral contraceptives prevented increases in weight and BMI and improved metabolic and hormonal parameters.', 'Myo-inositol acts as an insulin sensitizer, potentially improving metabolic and hormonal profiles in PCOS when added to OCP therapy.', '{97a00090-4d06-4adc-8e31-a16b5a90cba2,047286fd-7fb8-4f4e-b892-b20b47ac5276,c3b0884d-dfd1-4265-83a0-a06e0d2710e6,43d33f20-57e8-4848-a128-e6ef365a4768}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:07.170310+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:07.170328+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('35fc8509-2560-44bd-a5ca-b27de6264d31', '92bac47c-bc1f-4b7f-b0e9-d5459c82989d', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'safety', 'direct', 0, 0, 1, 0, 1, 'Only one source is cited (a single systematic review and meta-analysis), and the lone verified claim merely states that safety remains unclear. A single synthesis is not independent replication, and this claim provides no corroborating data at all.', 'Although the source is titled as a systematic review and meta-analysis, the verified claim only conveys that safety is unclear and that prior reviews focused on non-PCOS populations. No actual outcome data or design strength supporting a safety finding is presented in the claim.', 'PCOS is named directly, but the intervention is ''unspecified'' and the claim refers vaguely to ''treatments''/''anti-androgens'' without identifying a specific drug acting on PCOS safety. The drug is not clearly pinned down.', 'No mechanism of any safety effect is asserted or evidenced; the claim only notes that safety remains unclear. There is nothing mechanistic to support.', 'Only a single source and a single non-quantitative statement are provided, so directional agreement cannot be assessed. Per rules, a single study is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A single systematic review notes that the safety of anti-androgen treatments in PCOS remains unclear because prior reviews focused on non-PCOS populations.', NULL, '{7d1565a1-e553-49d2-a454-79de5d2482e1}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:13.933457+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:13.933487+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('3e6d03f8-dcc1-4e86-af68-1bd6410a2986', '3c56ac32-c154-4590-a85f-5a1ca8f3b790', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules, a single SR/MA caps at 1.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, which qualifies as the highest rigor tier. Design strength is high even though only one synthesis is cited.', 'The claim names both combined oral contraceptive pills (COCPs) and polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) directly. Both intervention and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The claim ties COCPs to mitigating hyperandrogenism-related symptoms, a plausible hormonal mechanism. However the mechanism is asserted rather than directly evidenced with mechanistic data in the quote.', 'Only a single source (one meta-analysis) is provided, so directional agreement across independent studies cannot be assessed. Per rules, a single source defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs indicates combined oral contraceptive pills may reduce hyperandrogenism-related symptoms in women with PCOS.', 'COCPs may suppress ovarian androgen production and raise sex-hormone-binding globulin, reducing free androgen and thereby hyperandrogenism-related symptoms.', '{908d7062-1476-4217-98b9-ea280575a497}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:14.796801+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:14.796831+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('8d5e4977-fe96-4a16-9aa3-be27ea992e4f', '2d9df8fe-d9e4-4952-84a1-af7d345c4198', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'All three claims derive from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials. Per scoring rules, a single synthesis scores 1 and does not count the pooled trials as independent sources.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, the highest rigor tier. This warrants a score of 2.', 'The claims explicitly name both anti-androgens and PCOS/hyperandrogenism-related symptoms. Both the intervention and condition are directly identified.', 'The claims state anti-androgens mitigate hyperandrogenism-related symptoms, implying an anti-androgen mechanism against androgen-driven symptoms, which is plausible. However, no explicit mechanistic evidence is detailed in the quotes.', 'Claims show a nuanced direction: anti-androgens may help symptoms but are not preferred over COCPs except in specific scenarios. Within this single meta-analysis the findings are coherent, so a neutral score of 1 applies.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs found anti-androgens may mitigate hyperandrogenism-related symptoms of PCOS but are not preferred over combined oral contraceptives except when COCPs are contraindicated, poorly tolerated, or inadequately effective.', 'Anti-androgens reduce androgen activity, thereby mitigating hyperandrogenism-driven symptoms such as hirsutism in PCOS.', '{65c631d1-96ba-4e12-95f8-dc0796dfbce0,1e9732fd-f8c7-4e4c-b87e-1f5def13e269,e3a8853d-9321-497b-a1f9-cd63fcd66700}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:15.308078+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:15.308132+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('9b0a674b-f0ee-456d-86da-3c4124455985', '40b16173-d1fb-4199-bc46-d064107fe48d', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, which counts as one synthesis source rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules, a single meta-analysis scores 1.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, the highest rigor tier. This warrants a score of 2.', 'Both the intervention (anti-androgens + metformin + lifestyle) and the condition (polycystic ovary syndrome) are named directly in the claims and source title.', 'The claims show an efficacy outcome (lower testosterone) consistent with anti-androgen action, but no explicit mechanism is detailed beyond the implied androgen-lowering effect. The mechanism is plausible but not evidenced in the provided claims.', 'Findings are mixed: testosterone was lowered with the combination, but no difference in hirsutism was observed versus comparator arms. These point in differing directions for different outcomes, so the evidence is not clearly consistent; given limited claims, a neutral score is assigned.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs found that adding anti-androgens to metformin + lifestyle lowered testosterone in PCOS, though hirsutism did not differ between combinations.', 'Anti-androgens reduce circulating/active androgen levels (lower testosterone), potentially augmenting metformin and lifestyle effects in PCOS.', '{d1c142bc-dbf7-43d7-aa3f-5e7b898ee991,310e27ef-9ef6-40e3-88f4-00449b910ee5}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:18.995852+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:18.995884+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('feaaef60-ad0c-431f-b83a-3d03f0d1bcc3', 'add8e0f7-2aba-45af-a7ce-12124b3fa77f', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules a single SR/MA scores 1, not 2.', 'The source is explicitly a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, the highest design tier. This warrants a rigor score of 2.', 'The claim directly names anti-androgens combined with COCP and the condition PCOS. Both intervention and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The claim reports a measured safety outcome (poorer lipid profiles) but no mechanism for how anti-androgens worsen lipids is asserted or evidenced in the quote. A lipid effect is biologically plausible, so plausibility is scored 1.', 'Only a single pooled finding is presented, with no second independent source to compare direction. Per rules, a single study/synthesis is scored 1 rather than penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs found that adding anti-androgens to COCP in PCOS resulted in poorer lipid profiles compared with COCP ± placebo.', NULL, '{005d1d7e-72d8-4225-8d7f-9bfbdbcfab51}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:22.099064+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:22.099130+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('412d7fe1-3efe-4941-a5d8-90e51bac6ff5', '23310854-9325-415c-a0f4-62347ae2eda3', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 1, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs (the anti-androgen review), which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. Per scoring rules, a single meta-analysis scores 1 and does not reach the threshold for 2.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, which is high on the design hierarchy. Claim 2 reports a pooled effect with a confidence interval and I2 = 0%, consistent with quantitative meta-analysis.', 'The condition PCOS is named directly in the source title, and hirsutism/androstenedione outcomes are described. However, ''daily use'' as the intervention is non-specific — the actual drug/anti-androgen is not identified in the claims, weakening specificity.', 'The claims show that more frequent (daily) dosing lowers androstenedione and improves hirsutism, implying a dose-frequency mechanism via androgen reduction. This is plausible and supported by the androstenedione data, but the underlying mechanism is not explicitly evidenced beyond the association.', 'Both claims point in the same direction (daily use superior to every-three-days dosing for hirsutism and androstenedione). They derive from a single meta-analysis source, so independent cross-source consistency cannot be established, warranting a neutral score.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs found that daily dosing was more effective than every-three-day dosing for hirsutism and produced lower androstenedione levels in women with PCOS.', 'More frequent (daily) anti-androgen dosing achieves greater androgen suppression, lowering androstenedione and improving hirsutism.', '{6b01b501-4cd7-4444-91a9-76410efb42b3,531f6f61-6b15-42ee-8056-94b2538aa8f9}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:23.495333+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:23.495359+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('66bf5b05-23a5-4ab5-bb5c-54e930fb578b', 'add8e0f7-2aba-45af-a7ce-12124b3fa77f', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The evidence comes from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. A single review scores 1 per the rubric, not 2.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, which qualifies for the highest rigor score. The design is explicitly a meta-analysis of RCTs.', 'The claim directly names anti-androgens combined with COCP and polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS). Both the intervention and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The single verified claim only reports ''no differences in other outcomes'' without articulating any mechanism for how anti-androgens added to COCP would act in PCOS. No mechanistic basis is asserted or evidenced.', 'Only a single meta-analysis is presented, so directional agreement across independent sources cannot be assessed and is scored as not penalized. The claim itself indicates no added benefit on other outcomes.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs found that adding anti-androgens to COCP produced no differences in other outcomes compared with COCP alone in women with PCOS.', NULL, '{99f2a1f3-548d-4573-aac0-cee2401129fe}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:24.524005+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:24.524031+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('12c7e7c3-be3f-47e3-beed-be74ff01e729', 'afa69e84-1146-4836-8bed-d29442024227', '25af577a-673a-4718-9c1a-5a433d8226c9', 'other', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The single source is a systematic review (''a systematic review'' in the title), which per scoring rules counts as 1, not independent replication. No additional independent studies are provided.', 'The source is a systematic review of efficacy and tolerability, which qualifies for the top rigor tier. The claim explicitly references a ''systematic review.''', 'Both the intervention (SSRI/SNRIs) and the condition (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women) are named directly in the verified claim and quote.', 'The claim only states efficacy/tolerability were evaluated; no mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the provided claims.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided with no directional results stated, so consistency cannot be assessed and defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review evaluated the efficacy and tolerability of SSRI/SNRIs for treating vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women, but the verified claim reports no specific outcome magnitude.', NULL, '{419f77c3-7ecf-4a39-b38c-9b9175a766bd}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:25.694066+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:25.694094+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('704788de-8773-46f9-945c-052c564c70bd', '1ee7ba1d-75b8-4754-be8a-a9fb12a64c0c', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women. A single synthesis scores 1 and does not constitute independent replication; the pooled trials within are not counted as separate sources.', 'The source is a systematic review (''The efficacy and tolerability of SSRI/SNRIs in the treatment of vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women: a systematic review''), which qualifies as high-rigor (meta-analysis/systematic review tier).', 'Both fluoxetine and the menopausal condition (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women) are named directly in the claim and source title.', 'The claim only states fluoxetine is less effective and a second-line option; no mechanism for its effect on vasomotor symptoms is asserted or evidenced in the provided claims.', 'Only a single source and a single directional claim are provided, so consistency across studies cannot be assessed and defaults to neutral.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review found fluoxetine appears less effective for menopausal vasomotor symptoms and should be considered a second-line treatment option.', NULL, '{b539a901-6f80-4de7-81c3-9f0cf22e6e28}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:30.212968+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:30.212995+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a0132e4b-86e8-45cb-949d-4dc8b1f0e8a0', '7f6ed8f9-842a-42ca-b224-7ca9e3fcf95a', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women. A single synthesis scores 1, as one review does not constitute independent replication.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies for the top rigor tier per the design rubric.', 'Both sertraline and the menopausal context (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women) are named directly in the claim and source title.', 'No mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the claim; it only reports relative efficacy without explaining how sertraline acts on vasomotor symptoms.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so directional consistency across studies cannot be assessed and is scored neutral.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review found sertraline less effective for menopausal vasomotor symptoms and recommended it as a second-line option.', NULL, '{807df520-12ea-42f8-b68c-8ad2a0781b24}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:30.497902+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:30.497928+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('30ef3fc9-a5f0-4eff-af4f-e47cc7507f4f', '32800eb4-818d-4b1c-a2af-70f499b5db43', '3d08eafb-9ddd-4669-a3bc-f80164f7f1c5', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'All claims derive from a single systematic review and meta-analysis of RCTs; a single synthesis scores 1, not 2, since the pooled trials inside it do not count as independent replication. No additional independent sources are present.', 'The source is a systematic review and meta-analysis of randomised controlled trials, which scores 2 on design. Results include weighted mean differences with 95% CIs and heterogeneity statistics.', 'Both the intervention (anti-androgens + lifestyle) and the condition (PCOS) are named directly in the claims and source title. Outcomes such as hirsutism, SHBG, and fasting insulin are explicitly PCOS-relevant.', 'Anti-androgens plausibly improve hirsutism and SHBG in PCOS via reduced androgen activity, a mechanism implicit in the outcomes measured. No explicit mechanistic evidence is described in the claims, so it remains plausible rather than evidenced.', 'Results are mixed: anti-androgens + lifestyle were superior to metformin + lifestyle for hirsutism and SHBG but NOT superior to placebo + lifestyle for the same outcomes. High heterogeneity (I2 = 74-76%) for several comparisons further limits consistency.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', true, 1, NULL, false, 'abstract', 'A meta-analysis of RCTs found anti-androgens plus lifestyle superior to metformin plus lifestyle for hirsutism and SHBG in PCOS, but not superior to placebo plus lifestyle for those outcomes.', 'Anti-androgens reduce androgen activity and raise SHBG, plausibly improving hirsutism in PCOS.', '{ebe7144d-2dd3-4002-ac5f-b14f0a60e2a3,32f9968a-cb67-42c0-b85c-aa363e57f5ee,5d5b6c9e-db6b-4ddc-9a2c-76c1981951f2,ab7e779c-e8a0-4138-95fb-a3fe23786a59,7b969b5d-0e28-492a-beb8-0538e21ba796,11fef5d9-1e11-4dfb-8f3e-44542b911b37}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:31.197033+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:31.197063+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('5e20283b-5020-4cb9-9ee7-36793a55d714', '389a935b-118a-4184-8353-dc7370c3070e', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 'Only a single source (a systematic review) is referenced, and the verified claim merely states response is variable rather than providing corroborated efficacy data. The vague claim does not establish independent replication across multiple studies.', 'The source is described as a systematic review, which would normally score 2, but the verified claim is only a generic statement about variable patient response, not a synthesized efficacy outcome. The supporting evidence is too thin to credit full meta-analytic rigor.', 'The claim names hot flashes/vasomotor symptoms directly, but ''drug therapy'' is generic and no specific drug is identified in the verified claim (the source mentions SSRI/SNRIs only in its title). The intervention is not pinned to a specific named agent in the claim.', 'No mechanism is described in the verified claim; it only notes variability in patient response. There is no asserted or evidenced biological pathway for how the drug reduces hot flashes.', 'Only a single source with a single vague claim is provided, so direction of results cannot be compared across studies. Per the n/a rule, a single source defaults to 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Exploratory', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review notes that patient response to drug therapy for hot flashes is variable, with no specific efficacy magnitude provided in the verified claim.', NULL, '{00360ea5-cf15-409e-bbcf-e6ee0cab1851}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:34.032081+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:34.032107+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a85e37af-d16e-4645-bdff-d5361b2606e4', '740685ea-e0b1-4f7c-b973-003430d2d24e', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Both claims come from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms, which scores 1 (one synthesis is not independent replication). No additional independent studies are cited to corroborate the 65% reduction figure.', 'The evidence source is a systematic review (''The efficacy and tolerability of SSRI/SNRIs...a systematic review''), which qualifies as a rigorous design (meta-analysis/systematic review level = 2).', 'Both the intervention (SNRIs) and condition context (vasomotor symptoms/hot flashes in menopausal women) are named directly in the claims and the source title.', 'The claims report efficacy (65% reduction, onset within a week) but state no mechanism for how SNRIs reduce hot flashes; the thermoregulatory/serotonergic-noradrenergic mechanism is plausible but not asserted or evidenced in these quotes.', 'Evidence derives from a single systematic review source, and both claims point in a positive direction; with only one source, consistency cannot be independently assessed, so n/a -> 1.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that SSRI/SNRIs can reduce menopausal hot flashes by 65% with onset within the first week.', NULL, '{f3cb44af-f8e1-494f-9edb-02fa2a8f5962,af399fa3-c307-4f4f-864f-f75d7462111a}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:38.141629+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:38.141644+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('3c86c127-d971-46c2-83ee-3719ef0232c2', 'ac3177b4-dd91-445b-bb43-15769c481a42', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms. A single synthesis is not independent replication, scoring 1; no additional independent studies are presented.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-rigor design (2). The claim aggregates evidence on efficacy of paroxetine for hot flashes.', 'The claim names paroxetine directly and hot flashes/vasomotor symptoms directly, satisfying both intervention and condition specificity.', 'The claim asserts paroxetine reduces hot flash frequency and severity but provides no mechanistic detail. A plausible serotonergic mechanism for thermoregulation is implied but not evidenced in the quote.', 'Only one source (a single review) is provided, so cross-study directional agreement cannot be evaluated; defaults to 1. The review groups paroxetine with other agents as consistently effective.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that paroxetine is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of menopausal hot flashes.', 'As an SSRI, paroxetine may modulate serotonergic signaling involved in central thermoregulation, reducing vasomotor symptoms.', '{cbc6ada7-5baa-4222-8aaf-53044a219e8f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:38.657394+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:38.657425+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('69983f97-03da-4585-9c2a-7cbc200412dc', 'e6727c59-a55a-4e1e-ac88-8ea457c7afd8', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Both claims derive from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms. A single synthesis counts as 1, not independent replication of distinct sources. No other independent studies are cited.', 'The evidence comes from a systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs in menopausal women, which qualifies as high-rigor synthesis design. This warrants a score of 2.', 'The claims explicitly name SSRIs and the menopausal vasomotor symptoms (hot flashes) in menopausal women. Both the drug class and condition are directly named.', 'The claims state quantitative efficacy (65% reduction, onset within first week) but no mechanism is described in the quotes. A serotonergic effect on thermoregulation is plausible but not articulated here, so plausibility is scored as plausible/asserted.', 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review, so cross-study directional agreement cannot be independently assessed. Per rubric, a single source is scored 1 (n/a, not penalized).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that SSRIs/SNRIs can reduce menopausal hot flashes by up to 65%, with onset of benefit within the first week.', NULL, '{524cdefb-1eed-49cd-b6b3-feecd5abdccb,0eea0b3b-b508-4a2b-89ac-2d50b0594d4e}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:38.905806+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:38.905833+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('39354af3-0aa5-43ab-8740-d473598f9ac8', '3956d951-aa1c-47d6-8dfd-024f5d6c617d', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms. A single synthesis scores 1 and does not count as independent replication; no additional independent studies on citalopram specifically are shown.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-rigor design (score 2). However, only a general efficacy statement is provided without effect sizes or pooled estimates.', 'Both citalopram and hot flashes are named directly in the verified claim, which explicitly lists citalopram among agents effective for hot flash frequency and severity.', 'The claim asserts citalopram reduces hot flash frequency and severity but provides no explicit mechanism. SSRIs plausibly affect thermoregulation via serotonergic modulation, but no mechanistic evidence is given in the quote.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so direction of results cannot be cross-compared. Per scoring rules, a single study/source is scored 1 and not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that citalopram is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of hot flashes in menopausal women.', 'As an SSRI, citalopram may modulate serotonergic pathways involved in central thermoregulation, reducing vasomotor symptoms.', '{9b211e76-aca6-4997-98ac-6fd6721ed198}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:42.582015+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:42.582038+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('ecbc4e44-1c3f-4e70-bc0f-4cd6ae292732', 'f02367ca-3bca-43af-80db-0a713a8ba6d7', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review pooling SSRI/SNRI trials, which counts as one non-independent synthesis (score 1, not 2). No independent corroborating sources are shown for escitalopram specifically.', 'The source is a systematic review of SSRI/SNRI efficacy in menopausal women, which qualifies as high-rigor design (meta-analytic/systematic synthesis).', 'Escitalopram is named directly alongside hot flashes/vasomotor symptoms, so both drug and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The claim asserts effectiveness in reducing frequency and severity of hot flashes but provides no explicit mechanistic detail; SSRI modulation of thermoregulation is plausible but not evidenced in the quote.', 'Only a single source is provided, so directional consistency across independent studies cannot be assessed; scored neutral per single-source rule.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that escitalopram is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of hot flashes in menopausal women.', 'SSRI-mediated serotonergic modulation may influence central thermoregulation to reduce vasomotor symptoms.', '{59911512-a9b0-4c6e-b162-d1e7e8db07a3}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:45.338883+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:45.338910+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('cd2e3d52-b111-4e31-ad46-51070d4564c5', '6dec39ef-5927-490f-8183-89340da7d9d1', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review stating that venlafaxine and other agents reduce hot flash frequency and severity. A single synthesis counts as 1, not independent replication. No additional independent studies are provided.', 'The source is a systematic review of SSRI/SNRI efficacy for vasomotor symptoms, which qualifies as high-rigor evidence (meta-analysis/systematic review level).', 'The claim names venlafaxine specifically and the condition (hot flashes/vasomotor symptoms) directly, both clearly identified.', 'The claim asserts efficacy but does not detail a mechanism; SNRI modulation of thermoregulatory neurotransmitters is a plausible but unstated pathway here. No mechanistic evidence is cited in the claim.', 'Only a single source/claim is provided, so directional consistency across studies cannot be assessed; scored neutral per single-study rule.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that venlafaxine is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of hot flashes in menopausal women.', NULL, '{fc711e7a-0e23-49cc-843b-54fc4b238c1c}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:45.838509+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:45.838538+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('6a4a2dca-5e87-4e4d-b9a9-344a39405b81', '6a6ec540-0d18-4f4b-9234-63e6f9d9dbc7', '06184ba7-3930-48f7-bc4d-6bf153f1387a', 'efficacy', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 1, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review pooling SSRI/SNRI trials. A single synthesis is not independent replication, so it scores 1 rather than 2.', 'The source is a systematic review of SSRI/SNRI efficacy for vasomotor symptoms, which qualifies as high-design rigor (meta-analysis/systematic review level).', 'The claim names desvenlafaxine directly and addresses hot flashes (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women), so both drug and condition are explicitly specified.', 'As an SNRI, desvenlafaxine''s reduction of hot flashes is mechanistically plausible via serotonergic/noradrenergic thermoregulation, but no explicit mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the claim.', 'Only a single source is presented, so directional consistency across independent studies cannot be assessed; default n/a score applies.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review concludes that desvenlafaxine is effective in reducing the frequency and severity of hot flashes in menopausal women.', 'As an SNRI, desvenlafaxine may modulate serotonergic and noradrenergic pathways involved in central thermoregulation, reducing vasomotor symptoms.', '{2ddc6ae1-2612-4335-8feb-25d4c2916d87}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:48.083320+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:48.083352+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('4265e6b1-31cb-41b6-85e1-5ed92f43b3dc', 'ac3177b4-dd91-445b-bb43-15769c481a42', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms. A single synthesis scores 1, not 2, and there is no independent replication shown beyond this one review.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high rigor (2). However, the single claim provides only a qualitative tolerability statement without quantitative data.', 'Both paroxetine and the menopausal context (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women) are named directly in the claim and source title.', 'No mechanism for the favorable adverse-effect profile is asserted or evidenced in the claim; only a comparative tolerability observation is provided.', 'Only a single source/claim is available, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed; scored as n/a (1).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review reports that paroxetine appears to have among the fewest adverse effects of SSRI/SNRIs used for vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women.', NULL, '{7526cbe9-da7e-4cc7-9c92-812a915ce05f}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:49.306762+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:49.306909+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('a9c39fde-d7b1-401e-83da-fee4ed8e5110', '3956d951-aa1c-47d6-8dfd-024f5d6c617d', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'The evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs in menopausal women, which counts as one synthesis rather than independent replication. A single review scores 1 per the rubric, not higher.', 'The source is a systematic review (claim from ''a systematic review''), which qualifies as high-rigor study design. However, only a single qualitative tolerability statement is reported.', 'Both citalopram and the menopausal context (vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women) are named directly in the claim and source title.', 'The claim only asserts citalopram ''appears to have the fewest adverse effects'' without describing any mechanism for its tolerability. No mechanistic basis is provided.', 'Only a single source is provided, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed and the dimension is treated as n/a (score 1).', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women reported that citalopram appears to have among the fewest adverse effects.', NULL, '{85f36d44-fd38-4b16-8e29-9538b8dd6033}', 'claude-opus-4-8', 'b2637a5f35001f42', 'active', NULL, '2026-06-16T18:08:52.582882+00:00', '2026-06-16T18:08:52.582911+00:00') ON CONFLICT (intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO substrate_signals (id, intervention_id, condition_id, aspect, arm, corroboration_score, rigor_score, specificity_score, plausibility_score, consistency_score, corroboration_rationale, rigor_rationale, specificity_rationale, plausibility_rationale, consistency_rationale, female_applicability_band, female_applicability_multiplier, female_applicability_rationale, confidence_tier, contradiction_flag, num_contradictions, precision_note, needs_fulltext, source_tier, synthesis_summary, mechanism_hypothesis, claim_ids, model_name, prompt_hash, status, off_topic_reason, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('eb3ecfd4-5240-41bf-b21c-edc0dfccc138', 'f02367ca-3bca-43af-80db-0a713a8ba6d7', 'e3758034-fa92-40a3-af17-80fbbdecb0d6', 'safety', 'direct', 1, 2, 2, 0, 1, 'Evidence comes from a single systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for vasomotor symptoms in menopausal women. A single synthesis scores 1 and does not constitute independent replication. Only one claim is provided.', 'The source is a systematic review, which qualifies as high-rigor design (meta-analysis/systematic review = 2). However, no quantitative pooled data or risk estimates are presented in the claim.', 'The claim names escitalopram directly and concerns menopausal women (vasomotor symptoms of menopause). Both intervention and condition are explicitly identified.', 'The claim is a comparative tolerability statement with no mechanism described for why escitalopram has fewer adverse effects. No biological mechanism is asserted or evidenced in the quote.', 'Only a single source/claim is available, so directional agreement across studies cannot be assessed. Per scoring rules, a single study defaults to 1 and is not penalized.', 'F1', 1.0, 'Evidence generated in women (female population, ~100% female).', 'Moderate', false, 0, 'no sample size or CI in source — precision unknown, flagged for full text', true, 'abstract', 'A systematic review of SSRI/SNRIs for menopausal vasomotor symptoms reports that escitalopram is 